<HEADLINE> HK News Media Hail CPPCC Annual Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong-based news media
today presented a variety of TV programs, photos and commentaries
and stories, hailing the opening of the Fifth Session of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
Two major local TV stations, TVB and Asia TV, telecast the
opening ceremony of the CPPCC's session with a focus on the scenes
of mourning for Deng Xiaoping on Thursday and Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Major newspapers here also devoted huge pages to the opening of
the CPPCC annual session with photos and articles to cherish the
memory of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Commercial Daily carried the speech made by Chairman
of the CPPCC's national committee Li Ruihuan expounding Deng
Xiaoping's thought about the work of the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
It also carried an article by Director of Xinhua News Agency
Hong Kong Branch Zhou Nan on recalling Deng's presence at a
special session of the United Nations General Assembly in 1974 and
his wisdom and foresight on handling the question of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Ta Kung Pao carried a commentary which says that the opening of
the fifth session of the eighth CPPCC National Committee and the
forthcoming session of the National People's Congress (NPC) are of
great significance.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that the two sessions will make
preparations for the formation of the Ninth NPC and CPPCC which
will function at the turning years between the 20th and 21st
centuries.
</P>
<P>
It said that the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region to implement the principles of "One Country,
Two Systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and "a
high-degree of autonomy" represents the first step in China's
reunification.
</P>
<P>
It said that in the latter half of this year the Communist
Party of China will hold its 15th National Congress which will
formulate strategic plans to lead the Chinese nation into the next
century.
</P>
<P>
The paper also stressed the role of the CPPCC in politics in
the Chinese mainland and the CPPCC members' contribution to Hong
Kong's returning to her motherland and the reunification of China.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
