<HEADLINE> Audi to Set Up Regional Headquarters in UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, February 28 (Xinhua) -- German's car maker Audi is
to set up a regional headquarters in the United Arab Emirates
(UAE), local newspaper Gulf News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters, to be located at the Airport Free Zone in
Dubai, the second largest city of the UAE, will be reponsible for
emerging markets in the Near and Middle East, Turkey and Africa,
the paper quoted Michael Renz, the newly appointed managing
director of the automaker, as saying.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters, which will be subject to a final
confirmation by the company's supervisory board meeting in March,
is to be launched by the second quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of Audi's attempt to extend its global reach
and directly serve regional markets through improved local
agencies, Renz said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
