<HEADLINE> On-line International Exhibition Launched in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 28 (Xinhua) -- A number of enterprises in
east China's Zhejiang Province are making an effort to access
international markets through a new channel.
</P>
<P>
The first on-line international exhibition in the province has
been set up and gone into operation this year.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, set up by the Zhejiang Provincial Department of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, is open to Internet users
around the clock through a server set up on the trunk line in the
United States.
</P>
<P>
So far, a number of foreign trade enterprises in Hangzhou and
Xiaoshan, two of the most rapidly developing areas in the
province, have logged on to the service, where they are connected
to the world's most famous import and export electronic billboard
and UN trade information bulletin.
</P>
<P>
The on-line service in China, still at the early stage of
development, has been booming in recent years. Government
statistics for 1996 show that the number of Internet users in
China had exceeded 40,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
