<HEADLINE> HK Dignitaries Depict Bright Prospects for Mainland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Dignitaries from Hong Kong's
different sectors gathered here today to cherish the memory of the
late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping and exchange views on prospects
of the Chinese mainland and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the reform and opening-up and the
modernization drive started by Deng and the concept of "one
country, two systems" designed by him has laid a solid foundation
for China's prosperity and reunification.
</P>
<P>
Allen Lee, head of the Liberal Party and member of the
Provisional Legislative Council (PLC), said the general situation
in China has been very stable and quiet in these days.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leadership has repeatedly stressed that they will
stick firmly to Deng's policies while the Chinese people have
vowed to continue to promote the great cause of reform, opening up
and modernization, he said.
</P>
<P>
The situation in China can only become better and better, he
concluded.
</P>
<P>
Wong Siu-yee, a PLC member, told the meeting that under the
guidance of the "one country, two systems" policy, Hong Kong's
smooth transition is guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
With the preparation work for the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region proceeding smoothly, the whole society
remains very stable and the local people are looking forward to
the great moment when Hong Kong returns to her motherland this
summer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
