<HEADLINE> Israeli Soldier Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 28 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier was
killed and three others wounded in fierce fighting between
Israeli troops and Hezbollah guerrillas in south Lebanon this
morning, the state-run Israel Television reported.
</P>
<P>
The casualties were inflicted when pro-Iranian Hezbollah
(Party of God) fighters attacked an Israeli outpost in the
eastern sector of the Israeli occupied "security zone" in south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The 1,100-square-kilometer zone was established by Israel in
1985 as a buffer against cross-border guerrilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
The wounded were evacuated by helicopters to the Rambam
Hospital in the northern Israeli city of Haifa. One of them was
reported in serious conditions.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli forces responded with heavy bombardment from tanks
and artillery. A few hours later, Israeli Air Force planes
raided suspected Hezbollah targets north of the "security zone."
</P>
<P>
Today's Hezbollah attack was the third fatal one since the
beginning of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
