<HEADLINE> Singapore Prime Minister Arrives in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong arrived here this afternoon on a three-day official
visit to Zimbabwe to strengthen economic relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
The visiting premier is later expected to have a tete-a-tete
followed by official talks with Zimbabwean president Robert
Mmugabe on bilateral, regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Gh Chok Tong, who is coming from South Africa, is accompanied
by his wife and an 80-member delegation of government officials
and businessmen interested in doing business in the country.
</P>
<P>
He was met at the Harare international airport by president
Robert Mugabe, first lady Grace, vice-presidents Joshua Nkomo and
Simon Muzenda and several government ministers.
</P>
<P>
A member of the delegation said the business people were
interested in investment and trade with Zimbabwe in areas such as
infrastructure, food processing, information technology and
clothing manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe and Singapore enjoy good trade relations. In 1995,
Zimbabwe imported goods worth 8.1 million U.S. dollars from the
fast developing east-Asian city state, while it exported goods
worth 6.5 million U.S. dollars. Zimbabwe's exports are mainly
tobacco, raw materials, manufactured goods, food and domestic
animals. Imports include machinery and transport equipment and
chemicals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
