<HEADLINE> Jilin Controls Industrial Pollution Effectively </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Jilin Province in northeast
China has achieved fruitful results in reducing industrial
pollution by controlling the total volume of pollutants discharged
and launching a "blue sky, clean water" project.
</P>
<P>
The province has adhered to the principle of giving priority to
preventing pollution and combining precautions with combating
existing pollution, bringing 757 sources of pollution under
control and closing down or removing 163 enterprises guilty of
serious pollution.
</P>
<P>
The province's overall capability of preventing and fighting
against pollution has improved a lot, with more than 70 percent of
industrial waste now treated, a rate nearing the country's average.
</P>
<P>
Its environmental protection drive is mainly focused on
industrial pollution, which has been the province's environmental
scourge due to its backward industrial technology.
</P>
<P>
It invested 518 million yuan (about 61 million US dollars) in
treating 327 pollution sources in the petrochemical industry
sector, and has built corresponding anti-pollution facilities
whenever it built, rebuilt or enlarged industrial projects.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
