<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members Discuss Work Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Members of China's top
advisory body today regarded a work report delivered by its
vice-chairman Thursday as substantial and encouraging.
</P>
<P>
The members, separated into 49 groups, said that the report by
Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), is
comprehensive.
</P>
<P>
They gave high credits to the CPPCC National Committee's work
last year and raised proposals for the handling of China's two
major events this year, namely, China's resumption of the exercise
of sovereignty over Hong Kong in July and the convocation of the
15th national congress of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
The members also discussed how the CPPCC can play a greater
role in China's political and economic life.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinbei, a member of the Standing Committee of the Central
Committee of the China Association for Promoting Democracy, said
that efforts should be made to strengthen links between inland
members and members in Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC should do more in promoting socialist ethical and
cultural progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
Members from ethnic minority areas and from religious circles
said they are inspired by the fact that the report mentions the
question of great unity among all ethnic groups several times.
</P>
<P>
Han Shenggui, a member of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee and president of the Islam Association of
Qinghai Province, said consolidating unity among ethnic groups is
an issue of overall importance and reflects the central
government's consistent policy.
</P>
<P>
"China is a big family composed of more than 50 ethnic groups,"
he said. "To make the people of such a big family happy and to
ensure a sustained and stable growth of the national economy,
there must be unity among all ethnic groups."
</P>
<P>
Zhang Shirao, a former vice minister of commerce, said that how
to further develop agriculture on the basis of an increase in
grain output last year is a very important study subject.
</P>
<P>
Many proposals made by CPPCC National Committee members last
year have been adopted by relevant government departments, said
Jin Chongji, who called for realistic proposals for state-owned
enterprise reforms and re-employment of displaced workers.
</P>
<P>
Xiao Guang, a song writer, said: "I support Vice-Chairman Ye's
report and agree on great unity and alliance of all ethnic groups
for a common objective."
</P>
<P>
He also proposed for an increase in financial input in
advancing ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
Wang Fen, a professor of Qinghua University, said that the
realization of the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000) and the
long-term goal for the year 2010 calls for the cultivation of a
large number of people with knowledge about basic sciences and
about management and marketing.
</P>
<P>
Members from Hong Kong said that they now feel even more of the
heavy task on their shoulders as Hong Kong will return to the
embrace of the motherland in over 100 days.
</P>
<P>
Wong Ker Lee, a member of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee and Chairman of Taiching International
(Holding) Co. Ltd, said that the overall situation is favorable
for a smooth return of Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that CPPCC National Committee members
from Hong Kong try all possible means to mobilize and unite with
all people that love the motherland and Hong Kong to support the
first chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region and the future Hong Kong SAR government.
</P>
<P>
More should be done to spread the Basic Law in order to bolster
the confidence of Hong Kong residents and of international
investors, Wong said.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC National Committee members from Hong Kong should improve
their efficiency in participating and deliberating government and
state affairs and reflect popular will to the chief executive or
relevant departments, in order to guarantee social stability and
economic development in Hong Kong, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
