<HEADLINE> Senior Party Officials Join CPPCC Members in Discussion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Two senior Party officials
today joined discussions of members of the Eighth National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), which is having its fifth session in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, state councillor and a member of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
and Wen Jiabao, alternate member of the Political Bureau, and a
member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee,
respectively joined people from the sports circle and the science
and technology circle in group discussions.
</P>
<P>
After listening to members from the sports circle, Li expressed
appreciation for their precious suggestions, which he said would
be very helpful to China's sports work.
</P>
<P>
"The years since the beginning of reforms and opening up in
1978 have witnessed a rapid progress in the field of sports in
China, which is a major component of socialist ethical and
cultural progress," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He added that sports reform should be carried out on the basis
of adherence to socialism, and must be compatible with a socialist
market economic structure.
</P>
<P>
During the discussion in the scientists' group, Wen called on
all people of the science and technology circle to have a clear
understanding of their eminent responsibilities, and play a
significant role in promoting socialist material, ethical, and
cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
"We should try to improve the general quality of the national
economy and raise the quality and efficiency of economic growth
through the application of science and technology," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, the government should pay special attention
to and show great concern for scientists and technicians in
money-losing enterprises, rural areas, and other disadvantaged
regions and sectors, while supporting middle-aged and young
scientists and awarding science and technology workers having made
outstanding contributions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
