<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 17:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian Defense Minister: Israel Uninterested in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Defense Minister
Mustafa Tlass has said that Israel's persistence in building
Jewish settlements and changing the demographic features of the
occupied Arab territories in Jerusalem and the Golan heights
showed its lack of interest in realizing peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
Today's Damascus press quoted Tlass, who is also Deputy
Commander-in-Chief of Syria's armed forces and Deputy Prime
Minister, as making the remarks during an inspection tour of
certain Syrian Army units Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tlass said that Israel's call for the resumption of
unconditional negotiations was a mere attempt to deny any previous
agreement and to take the peace process back to square one. This,
he said, is unacceptable to Syria or any other Arab states.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister reaffirmed that such practices would not
help Israel reap any benefits. They would rather prompt Syria and
the Arabs to adhere to their legitimate rights and further
entrench their commitment to a just and comprehensive peace.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Syria's adherence to the peace process in line
with the principles upon which the process was initiated. Syria,
he added, is keen on maintaining the peace process in accordance
with relevant U.N. resolutions and the land-for-peace formula.
</P>
</TEXT>
