ISLAMABAD -- The death toll from the earthquake which jolted
central Pakistan early Friday rose to 41, according to official
figures.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin said Friday that he
doubts that the 1997 federal budget targets can be met and called
for "real and profound" reforms in the military.
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Slovenia's parliament on Thursday approved by a
slender majority Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek's new coalition
government, ending a three-month-old crisis following the
country's November general elections last year. 
