<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-28 17:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Northwest Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 28 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring about
six degrees on the open-ended Richter scale jolted northwest Iran
at 16:31 local time (13:01 GMT) today, an official report said
here today.
</P>
<P>
The Seismographic Institute of Tabriz reported that the quake
occurred at the suburban areas of Ardebil city, about 600 kilometers
northwest of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the tremor,
which lasted for about 15 seconds, panicked people and sent
them out into the streets.
</P>
<P>
Based on reports available, the quake has caused loss of
property and casualties in certain suburban villages. But the
number of casualties is not immediately available.
</P>
<P>
Several aftershocks followed the 6-degree tremor.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, an earthquake measuring 5.5 degrees
on the Richter scale shook the western city of Sanandaj 420
kilometers northwest of Tehran at 16:28 hours local time (12:58
GMT).
</P>
<P>
However, no information on possible casualties or damage to
properties has yet been obtained.
</P>
<P>
The tremor measuring about four degrees on the open-ended
Richter scale jolted parts of northern Gilan province at 16:30
hours local time (13:00 GMT).
</P>
<P>
It affected the city of Rasht, Fouman, Shaft, Some'eh-Sara
and part of Khomam, Sangar and Kouchesfahan.
</P>
<P>
This is the second major earthquake within a month. On
February 4, the quake measuring 6.1 degrees on the Richter
scale jolted northern Khorasan province, killing a total of 86
people and injuring hundreds others.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 village suffered varying degrees of destruction,
some totally razed. Over 11,000 houses were damaged, rendering
thousands homeless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
