<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Trade Show Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 28 (Xinhua) -- A Bangladesh trade
exhibition opened here today to display the country's various
exportable products with the objective of promoting mutual trade
investment between Nepal and Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The five-day Bangladesh Single Country Exhibition, organized by
the Export Promotion Bureau of Bangladesh, is displaying items
including garments, textiles, cosmetics, handicrafts, jute and
leather products, medicines and electrical equipment from more
than 20 trading firms of Bangladesh, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Opening the event, Nepali Prime Minister Sher Bahadur Deuba
expressed his belief that the exhibition will contribute to
promoting joint investment and bilateral trade between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade between Nepal and Bangladesh has been on the
rise remarkably with a surplus in Bangladesh's favor since the two
countries signed trade and transit agreements in 1976, Nepali
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal's trade with Bangladesh was around 19 million US dollars
last year with a deficit of 5.25 million dollars.  
