<HEADLINE> OAU Summit on Zaire to Be Held in Togo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) will hold a summit on Zaire in Togo on March 18-19,
OAU spokesman Ibrahim Daggash announced today in the Libyan
capital city of Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Tripoli quoted Daggash as saying
that the two-day OAU summit, to be attended by 17 African heads of
state, will examine developments of the situation in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that the decision on the convocation of the
summit was adopted during the last meeting of the OAU Council of
Foreign Ministers which concluded today.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Zaire have indicated fighting has continued
outside Kindu, considered a key target of the advance by rebels
led by Laurent Kabila toward Kisangani, a provincial capital and
Zaire's third-largest city.
</P>
<P>
The rebels took up arms after the government tried to expel
ethnic Tutsis from eastern Zaire. The rebels are seeking to topple
Zairian President Mobutu Sese Seko. 
