<HEADLINE> Angola to Resume Cooperation Relations with Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Angola will shortly sign
framework agreements with Romania, Yugoslav and Poland in order
to resume bilateral relations of cooperation with the three
east European countries.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Angolan vice-foreign minister
Sebastiao Isata to press circles at the airport upon his return
from his 7-day visits to these three countries. The agreements
will be signed within two to three months, he said, adding that
the main purpose of signing these agreements was to resume the
relations of cooperation with these countries which were severed
amidst the drastic changes in east Europe.
</P>
<P>
During his recent tour of these countries, he said, he had
had talks with leaders of these countries, and they all held
that is was necessary to resume their bilateral relations of
cooperation under the conditions of market economy.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, he said, he had also briefed leaders of
these countries on the peace process of Angola, and they all
hoped that peace will be realized in Angola as quickly as
possible so as to create more favourable conditions for the
development of cooperation. 
</P>
