<HEADLINE> China, Uganda Sign Letter of Intention on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- China and Uganda have signed
a letter of intention on investment cooperation between the two
governments.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Chinese Assistant Minister of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Yang Wensheng and Ugandan Minister of
Planning and Economic Development Richard Kaijuka signed the
letter on behalf of their respective government here today.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that the governments of the two countries
would encourage and support Chinese firms to invest in Uganda for
projects of joint ventures, co-production and/ or prorietary
nature.
</P>
<P>
