financial support for the above Chinese firms and urge them to
abide by the local laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that the Ugandan government would extend
concessional terms and provide necessary facilities as provided
under the investment code and other laws applicable.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing ceremony, Yang Wensheng said that the
economic cooperation between the two countries can be further
expanded because there are still wide range of economic
opportunity existing between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said development of national economy closely links with
enterprises, hoping that enterprisers of the two countries visit
each other in future so that relations of the two countries in
economic field can be strengthened even further.
</P>
<P>
Kaijuka in his speech reiterated his attitude of welcoming
Chinese enterprises to invest more fund in Uganda in a bid to
exploit the country's natural resources.
</P>
<P>
Before the signing ceremony, enterprisers of the two countries
discussed ways to strengthen economic relations between the two
countries. 
</P>
