<HEADLINE> Earthquake Kills 100, Injures 250 in Northwest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 28 (Xinhua) -- At least 100 people were killed
and 250 others injured in an earthquake measuring six degrees on
the Richter scale that hit Northwestern Iran today.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Tehran Radio reported that the earthquake
inflicted 40 to 80 percent damages on dozens of villages of
East Azarbaijan, about 600 kilometers northwest of Tehran.
