The report said that the rescue teams have been mobilized
to help the people hit by the earthquake, which occurred at
16:31 hours local time (13:01 GMT) today.
</P>
<P>
The Seismographic Institute of Tabriz reported that the quake
occurred at the suburban areas of Ardebil city, about 600 kilometers
northwest of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the tremor, which lasted for about
15 seconds, panicked people and sent them out into the
streets.
</P>
<P>
Several aftershocks followed the 6-degree tremor.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, an earthquake measuring 5.5 degrees
on the Richter scale shook the western city of Sanandaj 420
kilometers northwest of Tehran at 16:28 hours local time (12:58
GMT).
</P>
<P>
The quake affected the city of Rasht, Fouman, Shaft, Some'eh-Sara
and part of Khomam, Sangar and Kouchesfahan.
</P>
<P>
This is the second major earthquake within a month. On
February 4, a quake measuring 6.1 degrees on the Richter
scale jolted northern Khorasan province, killing a total of 86
people and injuring hundreds others.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 village suffered varying degrees of destruction,
some totally razed. Over 11,000 houses were damaged, thousands
became homeless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
