<HEADLINE> Norway to Finance Road Rehabilitation in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Royal Norwegian
government will finance the rehabilitation of Chalinze-Melela
highway at a cost of six million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued here today by the Norwegian
embassy, the rehabilitation work on the section covering Coast
and Morogoro regions will start in this financial year beginning
July.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that financing of the highway is part of
the Norwegian government support to the four years' second road
sector program (RSP) under the Ministry of Works.
</P>
<P>
The RSP program is part of the multi-million Dollars'
integrated road project (IRP) launched in 1991 and financed by a
number of individual, bilateral and multilateral donors.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the second RSP program, starting July,
marks the end of the first RSP program also financed by Norwegian
government which started way back in 1991.
</P>
<P>
It said that in the first RSP, the Norwegian government
managed to finance successful the rehabilitation of Same-Himo
road and currently is financing costs of engineering and
supervision on Himo-Arusha trunk road.
</P>
<P>
The costs involved in the engineering and supervision work of
the trunk road amounting to 2.5 million Dollars, the statement
added. 
</P>
