<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Farmers Urged to Prepare for Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's National
Meteorological Services Agency today advised local farmers to
cultivate drought-resistant crops during the small rainy season
amid scarce rainfall and varied distribution.
</P>
<P>
Based on the weather forecast for this year's small rainy
season which began in mid-February, the agency said farmers must
carefully apply fertilizers and use plain land that can hold
water for cultivation.
</P>
<P>
Since no rains came this month, farmers should also prepare
animal fodder and farmland for cultivation during the season, it
urged.
</P>
<P>
According to the weather forecast, rainfall distribution in
the coming month or March varies from 50-100 millimeters to 20-30
millimeters.
</P>
<P>
During Ethiopia's small rainy season, which lasts from around
mid-February to May, farmers, mainly cultivating maize and
sorghum, produce about 10 percent of the country's crops.
</P>
</TEXT>
