<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urrutia Sets Indoor Triple Jump World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Cuban Alliacer Urrutia set a new
world indoor record of the men's triple jump when he flied 17.83
meters at the Sindelfingen athletics meeting in Sindelfingen,
Germany on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The previous best of 17.77 was set by Russian Leonid Voloshin
in Grenoble, France in February 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
