<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7th East China Trade Fair To Open March 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh East China Export
Commodity Trade Fair, China's biggest regional export commodity
fair, will be opened in this economic center of the country on
March 5.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,537 exhibition stands and booths at the Shanghai
World Trade Center have been booked by some 1,500 enterprises from
35 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee of the fair has invited 43,000
overseas businessmen from more than 140 countries and regions to
this annual event.
</P>
<P>
Commodities such as foodstuffs, livestock products, light
industrial products, textiles, garments, machinery, electronics,
hardwares, mineral products, medicines and chemical products will
be the main attractions during the event.
</P>
<P>
The fair is jointly launched by nine economically-developed
provinces and cities in east China, including Shandong, Jiangsu
and Shanghai, this year.
</P>
<P>
As the biggest of China's seven regional export commodity
fairs, the fair clinched 2.2 billion US dollars-worth of deals
last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another important regional foreign trade fair, the
Eighth Tianjin Export Commodity Trade Fair, is scheduled to open
in north China's port city of Tianjin on March 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
