<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao on Social Stability, National Unity and Ethnic Solidarity (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Senior Party leader Hu Jintao
today stressed the importance of promoting economic growth and
firmly safeguarding China's social stability, national unity and
ethnic solidarity.
</P>
<P>
Hu, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau,
and a member of the Secretariat, of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, today took part in a group discussion
attended by deputies from the Tibet Autonomous Region to the
Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), which is having its fifth
session in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Calling 1997 "a special year in the Chinese history," he said
it is of critical importance to do a successful job in various
fields this year.
</P>
<P>
He noted that economic development, center of all work of the
Party and the nation, is also a fundamental task for a new
socialist Tibet.
</P>
<P>
"We should always focus on economic development," he said,
adding that, proceeding from its specific conditions, Tibet should
further strengthen the fundamental role of agriculture and animal
husbandry and actively develop pillar industries with local
characteristics and advantages.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested that the autonomous region should make
greater efforts to strengthen infrastructural construction,
promote the two fundamental shifts in a down-to-earth manner, and
speed up the pace of opening up.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao on Social Stability, National Unity and Ethnic Solidarity (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He told the deputies that it is necessary to pay close
attention to, and effectively maintain, social stability in Tibet,
which is of great significance not only to the autonomous region
itself, but also to the overall situation of state security and
modernization process of the whole country.
</P>
<P>
"We must take a clear-cut stance to resolutely and firmly
oppose separatism, safeguard unity of the motherland, and work for
solidarity among various ethnic groups," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
It is also necessary to correctly understand and handle
contradictions among the people, and eliminate in time any factors
that could lead to instability, he noted.
</P>
<P>
"We shall give full play to the Party organizations' leading
role, and do a solid job in cultivating a contingent of
highly-competent cadres, with an emphasis on the building of
grassroots Party organizations in rural and pastoral areas," he
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"We must closely rely on the people of various ethnic groups,
bring into full play the initiatives of cadres from all ethnic
groups and people from all walks of life, and work with one heart
and one mind, so as to accelerate economic development, achieve
long-term stability and common prosperity for all ethnic groups,
and build a new socialist Tibet that is united, prosperous, and
civilized," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also called on Tibetan people to carry work forward at the
behest of Deng Xiaoping, who enjoyed love and immense respect in
the whole Party and the whole army, and among people of all ethnic
groups across the country, continue to push ahead with the great
cause of socialist reforms, opening up, and modernization drive
Deng initiated, and do a good job of everything in Tibet.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
