<HEADLINE> NPC Deputies Voice Wishes (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese lawmakers attending the
fifth session of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) here
expressed views on a wide range of subjects before the session
began this morning.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Ye Gongqi, who is also chairman of the standing
committee of Shanghai Municipal People's Congress, expressed
appreciation for China's economic performance in the past year.
</P>
<P>
He said, "For the first time the Chinese economy enjoyed a high
growth rate and low inflation, laying an extremely good foundation
for its future development; the margin of income increase for
peasants was greater than that for urban residents; and the
country's foreign exchange reserves increased. These indicate that
the central government has made an step forward in its ability to
regulate the national economy on a macro scale. I'm full of
confidence about the future."
</P>
<P>
Ye's view was shared by other deputies to the NPC.
</P>
<P>
Many of them talked about two major events that are to take
place in China this year -- the return of Hong Kong to China in
July and convocation of the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Peter M.K. Wong, vice chairman of the Chinese General
Chamber of Commerce in Hong Kong, expressed high appreciation for
the principles of "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" and "a high degree of autonomy" for Hong Kong
put forth by the late leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
"Though Mr. Deng Xiaoping has passed away, I believe the
principles he laid down for Hong Kong will endure. Only when the
motherland is strong and prosperous can Hong Kong's sustained
prosperity and stability be really guaranteed. Hong Kong will
have even broader space for development," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
