<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Krupp to Build Largest Stainless Steel Plant in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Krupp, a leading German
multinational, is planning to spend more than one billion US
dollars constructing the largest stainless steel plant in China, a
senior company official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The company is actively discussing this project with concerned
Chinese departments, Dr. Jooss, an executive member of the board
of directors of Krupp, said at a ceremony marking the opening of
the company's office in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Krupp, German's largest nonferrous metal producer and a
stainless steel giant worldwide, reported a business volume of
nearly 20 billion US dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
So far, the company has invested some 1.3 billion US dollars in
China. It has set up several joint ventures in Beijing, northeast
China's Anshan City, and south China's Guangzhou and Shunde
cities, covering machine building, complete sets of equipment,
iron and steel deep processing, and automobile and construction
industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
