<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Czech Communist Party Officials Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China (CPC)
and the Chinese people will unswervingly hold to the course
initiated by Deng Xiaoping, said Li Tieying, member of the
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, here today.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Miroslav Grebenicek, chairman of the
Communist Party of the Czech and Moravia, Li said the CPC and the
Chinese people will continue to rally closely around the CPC
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Expressing condolences over Deng's death, Grebenicek described
the late Chinese leader not only as a great man of his country,
but a great statesman renowned the world over.
</P>
<P>
Deng passed away on February 19 at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
Deng was the architect of China's reform and opening-up policy,
Grebenicek noted, and the Czech delegation has seen the miracles
resulting from the country's efforts to build socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a state councillor, thanked Grebenicek for the
condolences. He said Deng was a great Marxist and a "remarkable"
leader of China.
</P>
<P>
To boil Deng's multi-facet contributions down to one sentence,
according to Li, socialist China's present prosperity would be
impossible without Deng Xiaoping, just as there would be no New
China without Mao Zedong.
</P>
<P>
Li said Deng's series of economic concepts are a new
contribution to Marxist political economy, an important part of
the theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics and
a significant guideline for the reform and opening-up and the
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Grebenicek arrived here February 23 at the invitation of the
CPC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
