<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic Reaches Italian Indoors Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Goran Ivanisevic defeated German
David Prinosil of Germany 6-0, 7-6 (8-6) to reach the final of the
Italian Indoors tennis tournament in Milan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic raised his singles record for 1997 to 21 wins in the
rapid-fire match, which lasted one hour at the Forum in front of a
crowd fewer than 1, 000.
</P>
<P>
The world No. 5 Croatian ran his career record against the
world No. 59 German to 4-1 as he moved to within a match of
defending his second title of the year after winning in Zabreg
last month.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Ivanisevic will face the winner of another semifinal
match between the unseeded Sergi Bruguera of Spain and German
teenager Nicolas Kiefer.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic had it easy in the opening set but had to work in
the second, finally advancing from a service winner on second set
point after Prinosil saved one winning chance for the Croatian.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian's one-way win moved him into his 41st career
final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
