<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Die in Xinjiang Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, MARCH 1 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring six on the
Richter Scale rocked Jiashi County under the jurisdiction of Kashi
City in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region today,
killing two persons and injuring three others.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of buildings were destroyed, along with 26 head of
livestock.
</P>
<P>
The shock was the third severe quake to hit the area in less
than a year. The previous two killed a total of 36 people and
injured 170, according to the region's seismology bureau.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake could be felt across the county, and two
townships suffered the worst loss of lives and property.
</P>
<P>
Rescue work is underway and relief supplies are being rushed to
the county.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake caused no panic among the local residents, who
are constantly prepared for such contingencies in this
quake-susceptible region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
