<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts Sino-Portuguese Economic Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on Sino-Portuguese
economic and trade co-operation was held here today during
Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio's visit to this economic
powerhouse of China.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was attended by local entrepreneurs and a
Portuguese trade commission led by Mr. Costa, chairman of a
Portuguese foreign trade and investment committee.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and Portuguese businessmen held trade talks and
discussions on co-operation in the fields of pharmaceuticals,
environmental protection, new building materials, bio-engineering
and information.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume between Shanghai and Portugal reached 7.21 million
US dollars last year, a rise of 38.17 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
Portuguese businessmen had invested 2.55 million US dollars in
three projects in Shanghai by the end of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
