<BODY>
<HEADLINE> APU Decries Israeli Settlement Activity in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The Arab Parliamentary Union
(APU) today lashed out the Israeli decision to build new Jewish
neighborhood in the occupied Arab city of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
"The move comes in the context of Israel's persistence in
judaizing the holy city and stamping out its Arab and Islamic
identity," a statement issued by the Damascus-based APU said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli Ministerial Committee on Jerusalem Affairs
approved Wednesday the construction of new Jewish settlements of
6,500 homes in Har Homa of east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The statement urged the Arab governments to adopt a unified
position against the Israeli settlement policy.
</P>
<P>
It also requested all the parliamentarians worldwide to call on
their governments to condemn the Israeli move and bring pressure
on Israel to stop its settlement activity.
</P>
<P>
The APU document pointed out that all the recent Israeli
measures have constitute a flagrant breach of the UN resolutions
on the occupied territories and showed the Israeli aggressive
expansionist tendency.
</P>
<P>
The measures have made light of all the international
resolutions and conventions and the will of the international
community and constitute a grave threat to the Middle East peace
process, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli act may bring the region back to "furnace of
violence and tension" which are likely to explode at any time, it
warned.
</P>
<P>
The APU asked the UN Security Council to adopt a resolution
immediately barring the Israeli persistence in its expansionist
policy and changing the identity of the holy city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
