<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Advisers Eager to Air Views </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Members of China's top advisory
body, the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC) National Committee, are eager to air views and raise
suggestions before all their fellow members.
</P>
<P>
By 11 AM this morning, 218 people had applied to speak at
plenary meetings of the fifth session of the Eighth CPPCC National
Committee, which opened here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Applications for speaking are expected to exceed 400 when the
entry deadline arrives on March 8.
</P>
<P>
Speaking orally or in written form has been one way for CPPCC
National Committee members to participate in the running of state
affairs. Applications for an opportunity to deliver a speech
before a whole house of members have been on the rise in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
Liu Ming, who is responsible for arranging oral speeches, said
that the quality of speeches already received is better than those
of the past sessions
</P>
<P>
Most of the speeches focus on economic development, especially
on rural economic issues. Other keen tops covered by the speeches
include promotion of socialist ethical and cultural progress and
ideological education among youngsters and migrating workers from
the countryside.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to the motherland is another hot topic
of both inland CPPCC National Committee members and those
representing Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
A total of 36 members will be given a chance to deliver a
speech during the current session, which has 2,081 members.
</P>
</TEXT>
