<HEADLINE> Cholera Cases Rise in Zambia's Eastern Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Cholera cases in Katete district
of Zambia's eastern province have risen from 23 to 41 since the
disease broke out there last month, Zambia News Zgency (ZANA)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
ZANA quoted deputy district director of health Pius Chikuse as
saying in Katete today that the department of health in the area
is doing everything possible to ensure the death toll is
minimized.
</P>
<P>
Chikuse expressed his fears that the water-borne disease,
charecterized by intense diarrhoea and vomiting, which causes
dehydration leading to death if not treated within 24 hours, will
spread to other areas.
</P>
<P>
Cholera cases have been reported from various parts of the
country since the beginning of the current raining season in
November last year. 
</P>
