<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Wins Beijing International Road Race Relay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia defeated China and Japan
to win the Beijing International Road Race Relay here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian team, composed of Genet Giorgis, Birhanme Idere,
Addanech Erkelo, Asha Gigi, Merima Denboba and Gitenesh Urge,
covered the distance of 42.195 kilometers in two hours 15 minutes
and 10 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, with all members from Liaoning Athletics
Training Center, finished second at two hours 17 minutes and 17
seconds. The Japanese team were third at 2:17:23.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian team led from the start in the race, which was
divided into six legs of 5, 10, 5, 10, 5 and 7.195km. Abulkadir
Mhammed, manager of the African team said that all of his athletes
have done their best in the race. "Although it is a little bit
cold to us, " he added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which won the race last year, displayed a
surprise performance today, taking the second place with more than
two minutes behind the winners. However, Ma Junren, headcoach of
the team, said the result was normal. "Regarding the recent
training of the athletes, it is not beyond my expectation to
finish at this position," Ma uttered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
