<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Direct Shipping Across Taiwan Strait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese legislators express full
confidence in the establishment of direct shipping links across
the Taiwan Strait with efforts from both sides of the Strait.
</P>
<P>
The legislators, or deputies to the National People's Congress
(NPC) from east China's Fujian province and those of Taiwan
origin, are here attending the ongoing session of the Eighth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Since the central government issued management regulations on
shipping services and on agency arrangement for cargo transport
between the island and the mainland, some Fujian deputies say,
preparations for direct regular cargo container shipping services
between Fuzhou and Xiamen ports in the province, and Kaohsiung
port in Taiwan have entered a stage where attention is being paid
to specific matters.
</P>
<P>
Li Xiuji, chairman of the standing committee of the Xiamen
Municipal People's Congress, said that, with Hong Kong's return to
the motherland a short time away, direct shipping across the
Strait is inevitable.
</P>
<P>
Cargo shipping between Fujian and Taiwan has been conducted
through transshipment in countries like Japan and the Republic of
Korea since the 1970s. With the rapid development of cross-strait
economic and trade ties, the amount of cargo transport between the
mainland and the island reaches tens of millions of tons each
year.
</P>
<P>
It takes eight hours for a cargo ship to sail the
160-nautical-mile-wide strait from Xiamen to Kaohsiung, a sea
link that has been cut off for half a century.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that direct shipping will slash 30 percent of
the current cost and a large amount of time.
</P>
<P>
Direct shipping will not only benefit cross-strait economic
exchanges, but promote national reunification, said Fan
Zengsheng, a deputy of Taiwan origin and vice director of the
Shanghai Port Authority.
</P>
<P>
"If this major step (direct shipping) is taken, cross-strait
ties will be closer," Fan said, adding that direct mail, trade and
shipping links across the Strait will bridge feelings first, and
then facilitate national reunification.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Fujian province has made a lot of
preparations for direct shipping. Fuzhou and Xiamen ports, as
pilot ports designated by the Ministry of Communications for
direct shipping, have been adequately equipped for direct shipping
in terms of port conditions, ships, navigation and communication
facilities, and maritime affairs management.
</P>
<P>
The deputies urged the Taiwan authorities to give up the policy
of impeding national reunification by setting obstacles to the
establishment of direct shipping links, to comply with popular
will, and to take a cooperative attitude in solving technical
problems involved.
</P>
<P>
"We Chinese are very smart people. So long as both sides show
sincerity, all so-called technical problems can be solved," said
Fan Zengsheng.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Taiwan's shipping industry has also shown
enthusiasm for direct shipping, and several shipping companies
there have applied for consent from relevant government
departments on the mainland to run direct shipping services.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
