<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Many of the Hong Kong-based
newspapers continued their reports on the on-going session of the
8th National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) with a focus on Chinese President
Jiang Zemin's speech on Hong Kong affairs.
</P>
<P>
In the form of commentaries, interviews with dignitaries and
special columns, the newspapers noted that Jiang Zemin's
attendance at the group meeting of the CPPCC members from Hong
Kong and Macao Friday showed emphasis from the central government
on Hong Kong's transition.
</P>
<P>
