fully displayed the Chinese central government's resolution in the
implementation of the concept of "One Country, Two Systems" and
"Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
It said that Jiang Zemin's speech has greatly encouraged the
Hong Kong people and it will promote Hong Kong's smooth transition
in the coming months.
</P>
<P>
It said that with the support of the Chinese central government
and efforts of the Hong Kong people, the preparations for the
formation of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR)
are making progress.
</P>
<P>
With the framework of the HKSAR government being produced, the
Hong Kong people are increasingly becoming confident of Hong
Kong's future, it said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the Hong Kong people will unite to contribute to
the formation of the HKSAR and to a smooth transfer of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Commercial Daily said in a commentary that the
Chinese government listed Hong Kong's return to her motherland as
one of the two top priorities for the country in 1997, showing the
resolution of the third generation of the Chinese leadership with
Jiang Zemin at its core to handle well the question of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It said that the Chinese leadership will then handle well the
question of Macao as well as the Taiwan issue to achieve the
reunification of China.
</P>
<P>
It said that with the support of the central government and
joint efforts of the Hong Kong people, Hong Kong will see a smooth
transition and maintain long-term prosperity and stability.
</P>
