<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Expels Turkish Ambassador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran today asked Turkey to call
back its ambassador to Tehran in a retaliation for action taken
by the Turkish government against the Iranian ambassador.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Foreign Ministry also declared in its statement
that Ufuk Ozsancak, Turkish Consul General in Iran's northwestern
city of Orumieh, as persona non-grata for having engaged in
undiplomatic acts within a period of one week.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Iran's official Persian daily Iran disclosed
that Turkish Ambassador to Tehran Osman Koruturk and the consul
general to Orumieh may be expelled from Iran.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the move is in retaliation for the attitude
of Ankara towards Iranian ambassador in Turkey Mohammad Reza
Baqeri.
</P>
<P>
Some sources said that the Iranian ambassador was asked to
leave Ankara because of his strong statement about Islam and
fundamentalism, which aroused anger from the Turkish authorities
and mass media.
</P>
<P>
In fact, Iranian consul general in Turkey was expelled Thursday
and its ambassador also returned to Tehran from Ankara reportedly at the
request of Turkish government.
</P>
<P>
Last April Turkey and Iran had expelled four diplomats from
each side on charge of espionage activities.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, Iranian Foreign Ministry said in the statement
that the Iranian government would like to consolidate the
bilateral relations with Turkey on the basis of internationally
recognized principles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
