<HEADLINE> Xu Hu: Plumber Serving Neighborhood for 10 Years (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Xu Hu is one of the ten model
workers commended by Premier Li Peng in his government work report
at the opening meeting of the Fifth Session of the NPC today.
</P>
<P>
Xu is a plumber and electrician working for a governmental
house maintenance unit in downtown Shanghai. For the past 10 years
he has offered round-the-clock services to the neighborhood to
cope with water and electrical failures.
</P>
<P>
He publicized his commitment in June of 1985 that if there were
water or electrical breakdowns before seven o'clock in the
evening, residents can place an order in his designated boxes, and
he will come to their aid. And if things go wrong after seven
o'clock, direct calls to his home are welcome.
</P>
<P>
Xu has since then made some 4,000 home visits, usually after
his day work shift, for prompt repairs in thousands of households.
Every year, he could hardly spend the eve of the Spring Festival
at home with his family, the most important occasion for family
reunion in China.
</P>
<P>
After the publicity of Xu's meritorious deeds, a large number
of model workers are coming to the fore in Shanghai as a result of
the efforts to learn from him, and socialist ethical and cultural
progress has been greatly promoted in and around the municipality.
</P>
</TEXT>
