<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng cited 10 model
workers emerging over recent years, in his government work report
at the opening meeting of the Fifth Session of the Eighth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Following is a brief introduction of one of them, Qiu E'guo, a
model policeman from east China's Jiangxi province.
</P>
<P>
When he was demobilized from the army back in 1979, Qiu went to
Nanchang, capital of Jiangxi, to serve as a policeman in a local
police sub-station, in charge of the household registration work.
</P>
<P>
In the following 17 years, he paid visits to and made friends
with almost all families registered in his station, and became a
well-known troubleshooter in the neighborhood.
