worked at the grassroots level for 28 years and repeatedly given
up chances of promotion.
</P>
<P>
Wu, who joined the Communist Party of China (CPC) at age of 18,
is now secretary of the Party committee of the Tangzhuang
Township, and deputy secretary of the municipal Party committee of
the Weihui City in Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
He became one of the leading officials of Tangzhuang at 26. In
the next 28 years, he served local people whole-heartedly, and
made painstaking efforts to lead them to shake off poverty and
become prosperous.
</P>
<P>
The Party central departments cited Wu as a model Party cadre
at the grassroots level, and called on all Party members and
cadres, especially township Party secretaries, to learn from him,
so as to help enhance the building of Party organizations in the
vast rural area.
</P>
<P>
Wu was selected in 1994 to be one of the country's "100 good
servants of the people" by the Organizational Department of the
CPC Central Committee, which granted him the honorary title of
"National Model Party Worker" in 1996.  
