<HEADLINE> Tian Peifa: China's Model Teacher (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng listed 10 model
workers emerging over recent years in his government work report
at the opening ceremony of the Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Following is a brief introduction of one of them, Tian Peifa, a
model teacher of the Miao ethnic group, one of China's national
minorities, who exerted himself to the education of children in
the outlying and secluded mountainous area of southwest China's
Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
Tian is headmaster of a small village primary school in the
Songtao Miao Autonomous County of Guizhou. Despite harsh living
conditions and financial difficulties, Tian taught for 30
consecutive years tutoring the school, and brought up more than
700 graduates.
</P>
<P>
When the school was about to close owing to a lack of teachers,
Tian persuade his eldest son, who had found a well-paid job in
another province, to return home and assist him in teaching.
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, the son was later seriously wounded and killed
in a fight against burglars who broke into the school. Tian called
back his third son to succeed his brother and took up teaching too
in his school.
</P>
<P>
"School is my life, and I have nothing to complain about
because I am a Party member and a teacher nurtured by the people,"
Tian was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Tian's meritorious deeds has been commended by the Propaganda
Department of the Communist Party of China's Central Committee,
and the State Education Commission, which have called on teachers
across the country to learn from his dedication to education to
further promote China's education.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
