<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sainz, Eriksson Retire in Safari Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Spanish Carlos Sainz and Swedish
Kenneth Eriksson, both among the top world drivers, retired today
in a sensational start to the 555 Safari Rally Kenya, the third
round of 1997 World Rally Championships due to mechanical problems.
</P>
<P>
Sainz, a double world champion and leader of today's
competition, was out of on the first leg of the three-day rally as
he swerved to miss an animal and had his car's wheel punctured.
</P>
<P>
A wheel of Sainz's reddish orange Ford car was changed and
tightened within two minutes, but dust trapped between the rim and
the hub allowed nuts to work loose and wheel studs were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Ford Team has confirmed Sainz's quit and crew were lifted out
of section by a helicopter.
</P>
<P>
Sainz's incident took place 40 kilometers into section when he
got going 300 meters ahead of Eriksson, the winner of the latest
round in Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Minutes later, Eriksson hit a large rock at 130 kph, ripping
out his right rear wheel assembly. He motored on three wheels to
drop only 16 minutes on the fastest car.
</P>
<P>
However, the consequent damage to Eriksson's Subaru car was too
extensive to repair in the very restricted service time allowed
and thus forced Eriksson out of the rally.
</P>
<P>
"The mechanics performed miracles," said Eriksson's navigator
Staffan Parmander, "But we were just outside the time limit -- a
matter of a few seconds."
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi's Tommi Makinen also punctured and ripped out a
brake line, then crashed into a bank. But he still just managed
to hold off the Ford Escort Cosworth of Armin Schwarz.
</P>
<P>
Colin McRae, who carried only one spare wheel into the section,
punctured twice and had to battle on with one flat tyre. So local
driver Ian Duncan's Toyota Celica, which had started six minutes
behind him, was right on his tail at the end of the section.
</P>
<P>
Duncan had also gambled with only one spare -- "the section was
so rough, we tried to save weight," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, at the next service park he took a second spare wheel
on board.
</P>
<P>
Today's route, the same with the third leg on Monday, covers
584 kilometers and 406.10 of them are competitive sections.
</P>
<P>
There are lots of boobytraps and a large sandy river in the
first competitive section, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Safari Rally will run over 13 competitive sections and
2,400 kilometers of Kenya's spectacular terrain.
</P>
<P>
As many as 63 cars has listed for the main event and 24 for the
parallel Classic classes in the rally, representing a total of 22
motor makers with crews from 19 countries.
</P>
<P>
After two rounds of the 1997 WRC, Sainz leads the drivers
standing with 12 points, Eriksson and Italian Piero Liati have 10
each and Makinen has eight.
</P>
<P>
Subaru led the manufacturers' standing with 23, Ford was second
at 16 and Mitsubishi third 10 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
