<HEADLINE> Feature: International School of Lusaka (by Wang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 900 students with different
skin colors are studying in the Interntional School of Lusaka
(ISL).
</P>
<P>
The students are from 55 countries throughout the world
including Zambia itself, the primary school principal E. Ballard
told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The students are children of rich Zambians, of those of Indian
origin, foreign diplomats, representatives of international
agencies and foreign businessmen living in the country.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1963, the international school is one of the oldest
international schools on the African continent.
</P>
<P>
Teaching staff consists of over 70 professional educators from
12 countries.
</P>
<P>
The school is managed by a Board of Governors, nine of whom
are elected by ISL association. The association is composed of
the parents of students and of professional teaching staff.
</P>
<P>
The primary school program follows a standard English language
medium program and curriculum materials are mostly from Britain
and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Reading, language, scence, social studies and mathematics are
taught in primary school. Specialist teachers provide instruction
in music, art, physical education and computer studies.
</P>
<P>
The secondary school program offers a broad international
curriculum in Forms 1-3 (Grades 7-9) with courses in art,
computer studies, english, health, humanities, mathematics,
music, physical education, science and either French or Spanish.
</P>
<P>
The U.K. based International General Certificate of Secondary
Education (IGCSE) is a two year curriculum offered for Forms 4
and 5 (Grades 10 and 11). There is a separate English as a second
language program for those who require it before entering the
main school program.
</P>
<P>
During the course of the year there is a number of occasions
for interviews between parents and teachers, and there is also
regular written reports sent home. Parents can also contact a
teacher at other time to discuss about their children.
</P>
<P>
But the school fees are very expensive. Tuition fee for a
primary school student per term is as high as 1,000 U.S. dollars
and a secondary school student of Form 6 pays 2,000 dollars.
Many zambians can only get a salary of about 50 dollars monthly.
</P>
<P>
Primary school has no class in the afternoon and the students
can go to school three times a week to choose the activities such
as swimming, creative writting, draughts, extra French, field
hockey, language games, remedial maths, creative crafts, musical
production, football and cooking.
</P>
<P>
The ISL has a 33-acre campus and nine main buildings housing 63
classrooms, five laboratories, two libraries, three comuter rooms,
three art studios and staff recreational areas.
</P>
<P>
In view of the diversity of its students, the international
school of Lusaka tries to prepare its students to be world
citizens, free of prejudices of race, culture, national and
economic background, or religious belief. enditem

=03011153

=03011200
NNNN
20:00 20:00 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
