<HEADLINE> Ramos to Visit 5 South Asian, Middle East Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
will pay a 10-day state visit to five countries in South Asia and
the Middle East beginning on March 2, a news release from the
Presidential Palace said today.
</P>
<P>
The five countries are India, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Qatar and
Bahrain, Philippine Foreign Affairs Undersecretary Rodolfo
Severino said in the release.
</P>
<P>
Severino said that Ramos' visit is aimed to strengthen the
relations of trade and investments, science and technology, and
people-to-people exchanges, between the Philippines and the five
countries.
</P>
<P>
During the five-nation swing, his first trip for the year,
Ramos will be accompanied by several cabinet members, including
Foreign Affairs Secretary Domingo Siazon, Trade and Industry
Secretary Cesar Bautista, and other government officials.
</P>
<P>
Governor of the Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao and
Chairman of the Southern Philippine Council for Peace and
Development Nur Misuari and more than 80 businessmen will also
join the president.
</P>
<P>
Severino pointed out that the five countries have been
supportive of the Philippine government's peace initiatives with
various rebel groups.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he said, Pakistan, Bangladesh, Qatar and Bahrain
are members of the Organization of Islamic Conference, which
helped the government in forging the peace agreement with the Moro
National Liberation Front that ended nearly three decades of
bloody confrontation in the Southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The highlights of Ramos' visit, he said, will be his bilateral
meetings with the leaders of each country and signing of several
bilateral and private joint venture agreements.  
</P>
