<HEADLINE> Malaysian Police Shoot Dead Three Hired Killers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Police today shot
dead three Indonesians identified to be members of a hired killer
gang in a shoot-out in Shah Alam near here.
</P>
<P>
Police recovered a .38 special revolver, two kitchen knives,
several flashlights and a pair of handcuffs from them, the
Malaysian news agency Bernama reported quoting a senior police
officer.
</P>
<P>
Police investigations showed the killers, aged between 20 and
40, collected a fee of between 1,000 Ringgit (about 400 US
dollars) and 4,000 Ringgit (about 1,600 US dollars) to kill fellow
Indonesians, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The group, which had many sycophants who are being tracked
down, were high on the police wanted list for armed robberies and
rape of Indonesian women, the police officer said, adding many of
the rape cases were not reported to the police by the victims.
</P>
<P>
According to the officer, the gang active in the last two years
was involved in at least three murders of Indonesian nationals.
</P>
<P>
The killers, whose modus operandi differed from one incident to
another, were known for their brutal killings including severing
the neck and crushing the heads of victims, he said.
</P>
<P>
A police party in a patrol car spotted four men on two
motorcycles this noon and ordered them to stop but one of the man
fired a shot at the police.
</P>
<P>
Police returned fire and hit one of the man who fell to the
ground while the other three sped off.
</P>
<P>
Police gave chase and in the ensuing shoot-out, two others were
killed while another accomplice, who is armed with a revolver,
managed to escape on his motorcycle, he said.
</P>
<P>
Based on the red identity cards recovered from them, two dead
were identified as Azahari Mustam and Sadli Abdul while the third
did not have any personal identification documents.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, police are tracing the Indonesians who
hired the gang to kill others, according to the report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
