<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 10:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Protests USA for Nuisance in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian government lodged a
protest against the United States for its forces creating
nuisance for Iranian ships and vessels in the Persian Gulf,
an official report said here today.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the protest
was made by Maji Takht-Ravanchi, Iran's deputy permanent
representative to the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the letter by the Iranian government
to the U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan was circulated as a
document of the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Takht-Ravanchi stressed that the U.S. warships and helicopters
positioned in the Persian Gulf and the Sea of Oman
repeatedly created a nuisance for Iranian ships and vessels.
</P>
<P>
On December 9, 1996, after the ship "Iran-Shojaat" left
Bandar-e Imam and Khour Mussa region of Iran, it was inspected by a
U.S. warship.
</P>
<P>
The letter said that the U.S. warship contacted the Iranian
ship and ordered to reduce its speed and directed the ship
to a specific position.
</P>
<P>
It then inquired about the specific contents of the ship.
Following a thorough investigation, the ship was then allowed
to sail toward Bandar Abbas, it noted.
</P>
<P>
On January 8, 1997, two U.S. helicopters positioned in Buoy
two of Khour Mussa channel flew over the ship "Iran Matin"
which was navigating from Bandar-e Imam Khomeini to Bandar
Abbas, and through a VHF channel ordered the ship to change
its course toward Kuwait's waters.
</P>
<P>
After the Iranian ship contacted the control office in
Kharg island, it proceeded toward Bandar Abbas, the report said.
</P>
<P>
An American helicopter flew over the "Iran Tabriz" oil
tanker, which was leaving Buoy six of Khour Mussa channel on
the same date and ordered the ship to change its course,
said the letter adding after the oil tanker received a proper
course to follow from Kharg island, it sailed toward Bandar
Abbas.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian envoy voiced Iran's protests toward illegal
measures taken by the U.S. government and called for an end
to such actions. 
</P>
