<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- World Food Program (WFP)
yesterday approved a new relief food operation with 6.7 million
U.S. dollars for northern Uganda, reported the local daily "the
New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate recently that up to 220,000 people in
northern districts of Gulu and Kitgum have been displaced from
their homes because of the insurgency.
</P>
