that WFP has already given several batches of emergency food to
northern Uganda in order to stop malnutrition from spreading,
particularly among the young children and women.
</P>
<P>
WFP has pledged to help on a large scale in order to combat
the mounting problems being aced by those recently displaced
after an attack on Kitgum by the rebel lord's resistance army.
300 people were killed there.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan government has also been providing food and non-food
items to outlying areas of Gulu district since last July. 
