<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Relations with Western Countries (31) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- China hopes to further improve and
develop its relations with Western countries on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence, Chinese Premier Li Peng
said today.
</P>
<P>
In his government work report delivered this morning at the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), Li said
relations between China and Western countries have improved in
general, and positive results have been achieved in China's
mutually-beneficial cooperation with European countries in various
fields.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sino-U.S. relations had undergone relatively large
setbacks but are now evidencing a trend towards improvement and
development.
</P>
<P>
He said Sino-Japanese relations were once obstructed and
expressed the wish to see a normal development of relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said China wishes to see further improvement in Sino-U.S.
relations and the strengthening of Sino-European relations.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Western countries will benefit mutually from an
improved and further developed relationship, and different views
and divergences on some issues should not become an obstacle to
state-to-state relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
China is opposed to all acts of interfering in the internal
affairs of other countries, and stands for seeking common ground
while setting aside differences and for lessening differences and
expanding cooperation through more dialogue and exchanges, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
