<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stamp Market Relocated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- To boost local stamp trading,
Shanghai has moved a roadside stamp market into a nearby building.
</P>
<P>
The center, which is among the four-biggest in China, was
relocated in Yunzhou Mansion and has become a multi-functional
transaction market with first-class equipment, according to local
stamp trading officials.
</P>
<P>
It includes 120 transaction rooms and more than 400 counters,
totaling more than 3,000 sq m.
</P>
<P>
In the early 1980s stamp collectors spontaneously gathered at
certain places to exchange items from their collections, and a
garden around central Shanghai's Taiyuan Road was soon chosen as a
permanent stamp trading center for the public in October 1988.
</P>
<P>
In addition to stamp trading, the center also offers various
kinds of lectures and activities to spread knowledge of philately.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
