<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sets Up Air Traffic Management Bureau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The Air Traffic Management Bureau
of East China was established Friday here in Shanghai, China's
largest economic and financial city.
</P>
<P>
The head of the East China Civil Aviation Administration said
that the establishment of the bureau is aimed at strengthening air
traffic management and making the whole system operate more
smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The bureau grew out of the Air Traffic Management Center of
East China, which was in charge of the civil air traffic over
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The bureau consists of an air traffic management center,
meteorological center, aviation information center and
telecommunications navigation station.
</P>
<P>
It will draw up regulations concerning traffic management,
telecommunication, navigation and aviation information of its
administrative air space, and will provide safety guarantees and
other services for aviation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
