<HEADLINE> Indonesia Hopeful of Hosting 2006 Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia is ready to host the
2006 Asian Games but is doubtful of its chance of hosting the
Olympics in 2008.
</P>
<P>
The National Sports Council had promised to prepare to stage
the quadrennial event, possibly outside the capital, State
Minister of Youth Affairs and Sports Hayono Isman said here Friday
night after the four-day natinal sports coordinating meeting.
</P>
<P>
However, Hayono admitted that Indonesia would most likely be
unable to fulfill its ambition to stage the 2008 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"Hopefully, we can stage the event in 2012," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hayono said the government would observe the country's
situation in 2002 before submitting a proposal to the
International Olympic Committee to stage the event. 
</P>
