<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Coal Base Planned for Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province is to build a coal base with an annual output of 50
million tons of raw coal in the southern part of the province.
</P>
<P>
The five cities in the area have a combined proven coal
reserves of 8.2 billion tons, accounting for 66 percent of the
province's total.
</P>
<P>
Local officials have predicted that the coal-deficient province
will lack five to 10 million tons of coal each year in the 21st
century. So it deems the development of the local coal industry as
an urgent matter.
</P>
<P>
In the next five to 10 years, priority will be given to the
development of the Junlian and Guxu coalfields, a government
official said.
</P>
<P>
The former has a designed production capacity of 8.7 million
tons per year. Its development will require an investment of 14.7
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Guxu coalfield, near Luzhou City, will turn out one million
tons of coal annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
