<HEADLINE> 5 Bangladeshi Villagers Killed in Land Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- At least five people were killed and
15 others injured on Friday when the so-called Ansars, a
para-military group in Bangladesh, opened fire on a group of
agitated villagers at Savar county near the capital Dhaka,
according to police sources.
</P>
<P>
Police said the villagers illegally occupied a land which
belongs to an industry Partex group. The Partex group deployed
Ansars on the land in a bid to take possession of the land which
made the villagers angry.
</P>
<P>
The agitated villagers attacked the Ansar personnel on Friday
noon. The Ansars opened fire on the mob, leaving five people
killed on the spot and injuring others.
</P>
<P>
Seven Ansars were also injured in the violent incident at
Sadapur village in Savar county. They were admitted to different
hospitals and clinics in Savar and Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Receiving the news, police from Savar county rushed to the spot
and brought the situation under control.
</P>
<P>
No arrest has been made so far, police sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
