<HEADLINE> More Fire Cases Reported in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Altogether 137 fires broke out in
Myanmar in January, the official paper the New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,203 houses, two factories and one ware-house were
razed by the fires which caused 2,129 persons homeless, one dead
and five injured, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Out of the these fire cases, 116 were due to carelessness which
accounted for 84.67 percent, the paper added.
</P>
<P>
During this dry season, fire hazard is especially greater. The
authorities have taken precautionary measures for prevention of
outbreaks. 
</P>
