<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Fifth Session Opens  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The Eighth National People's
Congress (NPC), the supreme organ of power in China, started
convening its fifth plenary session in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,808 deputies to the NPC from across the country
attended the session's first meeting in the Great Hall of the People and
heard a report on the work of the government delivered by Premier
Li Peng of the State Council, China's cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Party and state leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi,
Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren
attended the conference and were seated at the rostrum.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, executive chairman of the session and chairman of the
NPC Standing Committee, opened the the session at 9:00 a.m.
</P>
<P>
After the playing of the national anthem, Qiao said that, on
the eve of this session, China's respected and beloved leader Deng
Xiaoping passed away unfortunately.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping was an outstanding leader enjoying high prestige
in the Party and the army and among Chinese people of all ethnic
groups, he said, noting that he is a great Marxist, great
proletarian revolutionist, statesman, military strategist,
diplomat, long-tested Communist fighter, chief architect of China's
socialist reform, opening and modernization drive, and founder of
the theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He said that Deng paid close attention to the development of a
democratic legal system and the system of people's congress in
China.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Deng's many important ideas on developing
socialist democracy, improving the socialist legal system,
adhering to and improving the system of people's congress are an
important component of his theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics, which should be taken as scientific
guidelines for building the people's congress system and
accomplishing its work well.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping's passing away has been an immeasurable loss to
the Party, the army and people of all ethnic groups, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
He called for all the NPC deputies to turn grief into strength,
carry on with their work at the behest of Deng Xiaoping and unite
closely around the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core, hold high the banner of Deng's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, and adhere to the
Party's basic line, in order to advance steadily the great
undertakings of socialist reform, opening up and modernization
pioneered by Deng.
</P>
<P>
At the request of Qiao, all present stood up in silent mourning
for Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
