<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Global Issues Should Not be Decided by Any One Power: Premier-32 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Global issues should be handled
through equal participation by all countries instead of being
decided by any one power, Premier Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
At the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's Congress
(NPC), which opened this morning, Li said at the turn of the
century, the international community faces many problems in
safeguarding world peace and promoting common development. The
settlement of these problems demands the common effort of all
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Government and people are ready to work
with all the governments and peoples of the world for a peaceful,
stable, prosperous and progressive new world.
</P>
<P>
At present, he said, the world situation as a whole is becoming
even more relaxed. International relations are undergoing major
adjustments, with the trend towards multi-polarity developing
further. The position and role of developing countries in
international affairs continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
The premier noted that it is the common aspiration of people of
all countries to establish a new international political and
economic order of peace, stability, fairness and justice.
</P>
<P>
However, he said hegemony and power politics still seriously
threaten world peace, stability and development, and local
conflicts and regional tensions still exist. The world economy is
growing steadily, but the gap between the poor and rich countries
is widening. It remains the major task of the international
community to safeguard world peace and promote economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Over the past year, China has pursued an independent foreign
policy of peace and has achieved positive results in its
diplomatic work.
</P>
<P>
China has actively participated in multilateral diplomatic
activities organized by the United Nations and regional
organizations and has made positive contributions to the
maintenance of world peace and the promotion of economic
development.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government has actively participated in and
promoted the process of the signing of the Comprehensive Nuclear
Test Ban Treaty. As a permanent member of the United Nations
Security Council, China has always adhered to principles and stood
for justice on major international issues, which has won extensive
praises and applause from the international community, he said.
</P>
<P>
China has fought resolutely against actions aimed at infringing
on its sovereignty and interfering in its internal affairs, and
has effectively safeguarded its state sovereignty and national
dignity.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and people are ready to work with all
governments and people's of the world for a peaceful, stable,
prosperous and progressive new world, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
