<HEADLINE> China to Push Ahead with Reform and Opening-up Initiated by Deng Xiaoping (33) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng called on
the entire nation to unswervingly push ahead with programs of
reform, opening-up and modernization initiated by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In his government work report delivered at the Fifth Session of
the Eighth National People's Congress, Li Peng said that the death
of Deng Xiaoping is an inestimable loss for Chinese people of all
nationalities and that Deng's contributions to the Chinese nation
will always be remembered by the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng concluded his report with a call to the Chinese nation.
He said, "We should turn grief into strength, carry on with our
work at the behest of Comrade Deng Xiaoping and, under the
guidance of his theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics and the basic line of the Party and under the
leadership of the Party Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin
at its core, keep in mind our fundamental interests, continue our
efforts, unite and work as one, and advance in a pioneering spirit
to further the great cause initiated by Comrade Deng Xiaoping and
achieve new successes in reform, opening up and socialist
modernization." 
