<HEADLINE> Road Accident Kills 6 in Northern Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Six people died and scores were
injured Friday after the coach they were traveling in plunged into
a 30 meter-deep ravine in Phitsanulok, northern Thailand,
according to a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The coach was being driven up a steep hill when it went out of
control and skidded off the road into the ravine, killing six
passengers instantly and injuring 47 others.
</P>
<P>
The report said the injured were taken to hospitals in
Phitsanulok and neighboring Loei province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Economic Structuring (34) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua)-- China will expedite the shift of
the economic structure and the mode of economic growth
conscientiously to ensure stability and maintain a sustained,
rapid and sound development of the national economy and promote
social development in an all-round way.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng made this remark at the Fifth Session of the
Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The report, which falls in 36 pages and 14,500 Chinese
characters, is divided into seven parts. Based on reviewing the
government work last year, Li Peng concentrated on such topics as
economic development, reform of the state-owned enterprises and
social development.
</P>
<P>
The report also elaborated such issues as to ensure smooth
transfer of political power and a smooth transition in Hong Kong,
to promote the reunification of the motherland and the foreign
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li said the year 1996 was the first year in implementation of
the Outlined Ninth Five-Year Plan and Long-Range Objectives
through the Year 2010. Under the leadership of the Communist Party
of China, he said, the people of all nationalities in China
united, worked hard and achieved fresh success in the reform,
opening up and the modernization drive, making a good start for
the accomplishment of the magnificent cross-century program.
</P>
<P>
A salient feature of China's economic development in 1996 was
the continued growth in national economy and inflation under
control. The gross domestic product (GDP) increased by 9.7 percent
over the previous year and price rises dropped from 14.8 percent
to 6.1 percent, much lower than the planned target for
macro-control.
</P>
<P>
Besides, China's economic restructuring progressed steadily and
the country continued to open wider to the outside world. New
achievements were recorded in science, technology, education and
in all other social undertakings. The standard of living of urban
and rural people continued to improve.
</P>
<P>
However, the Chinese premier also pointed out there still exist
quite a few conflicts and problems in the midst of economic
development and public activities, and there are also shortcomings
and deficiencies in the work of the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Economic Structuring  (35) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The problems referred to by Li Peng include: the foundation on
which macro-economic stability relies is still not consolidated
enough and unsound aspects of the economic structure are eminent.
The basis of agriculture is still fragile and the quality and
performance of the national economy as a whole remains relatively
poor.
</P>
<P>
"We are facing a fairly big pressure from population and
employment issues. Some state-owned enterprises are having
difficulties in production and operation and losses are on the
rise," he added.
</P>
<P>
Li also said that some more enterprises have completely or
partially suspended production, leading to a rise in the number of
laid-off workers. Central finance is confronted with considerable
difficulties; the relationship between income and distribution has
yet to be straightened out; corruption and other undersirable
phenomena remain serious problems, and bureaucratism, formalism
and proneness to boasting and exaggeration are spreading among
some government functionaries; public security is not good in some
areas. Li Peng called for attention to these issues.
</P>
<P>
After citing the above problems, Li Peng devoted two thirds of
his report to elaborating the goals set by the Chinese government
for this year's economic and social development and measures to be
adopted to solve the existing problems.
</P>
<P>
China has fixed the economic growth rate for the year 1996 at
eight percent as the target for macro-economic control and make
sure that price rise ranges are lower than they actually were last
year, he said.
</P>
<P>
To this purposed, Li said, China will continue to give priority
to strengthening agriculture, maintain a reasonable scale of
investment and intensify structural readjustment and strive to
continue carrying out appropriately tight financial and monetary
policies. Moreover, efforts will be made to open the country wider
to the outside world and keep improving the standard of living of
the people in urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The reform of state-owned enterprises has been listed as the
priority task in economic restructuring in 1997 and a pressing
task for the Chinese government, he said. The Chinese premier
dedicated more than one sixth of the report to this issue, which
has been rarely seen in government reports in the previous years.
</P>
<P>
Li acknowledged that China will closely combine reform,
reorganization and upgrading with better management, manage large
enterprises and conglomerates well and adopt a flexible policy
towards small ones and take different measures for deal with
varied situations. "All this should be done in order to achieve
pragmatic and effective results in reforming and developing
state-owned enterprises," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Economic Struc (36) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The six measures set forth by the premier include: concentrate
on rejuvenating large enterprises and enterprise groups; give
small state-owned enterprises still greater freedom; standardize
bankruptcy procedures, encourage merger of enterprises and promote
re-employment; increase capital and reduce debts through various
channels; conscientiously strengthen the operation and management
of enterprises; strive to help enterprises eliminate losses and
increase profits and vigorously promote the reform of the social
security system.
</P>
<P>
"It is important to improve socialist culture and socialist
ethics with a view to promoting coordinated economic and social
development," said Li, who also vows to make great strides in
science and technology, education, culture, public health and
sports as well as environmental protection and family and
development of socialist ethics.
</P>
<P>
Safeguarding social and political stability is indispensable to
the modernization drive in China, he said. In 1997, China will
improve all facets of public security, make greater, in-depth
efforts to combat corruption and to keep government employers
honest and industrious. Efforts will also be made to consolidate
and develop great ethnic unity, accelerate the modernization of
national defense and develop socialist democracy, improve the
socialist legal system and run state affairs according to law.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the Hong Kong issue, Li Peng urged to ensure a
smooth transfer of government and a smooth transition in Hong
Kong, and said that all preparations for Hong Kong's return to the
motherland are being made in an orderly way.
</P>
<P>
Turning to the issue of Taiwan, Li Peng said China will settle
disputes between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits through
political negotiations between the two sides and gradually achieve
the peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
In his government work report, the Chinese premier also set
forth China's basic policies in diplomatic work and the
international affairs.
</P>
<P>
To conclude his report, Li said, China will carry forward at
Deng Xiaoping's behests under the leadership of the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at is core, unite as one and advance in
a pioneering spirit to further the great cause initiated by Deng
Xiaoping and achieve new successes in reform, opening up and the
socialist modernization drive. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
