<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Science and Technology (17) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng said in Beijing
today that the Chinese government will continue to gear the work
of science and technology to the main arena of economic
development.
</P>
<P>
"We will try to do a successful job in the development and
application of technology, in research on high and new
technologies and their related industries, and in basic scientific
research, to help bring about a shift in the mode of economic
growth," Li told the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's
Congress, which opened here today, in his government work report.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government would focus on the research
and exploitation of applied technology, decide on key scientific
and technological projects in light of market demand and the needs
of key state projects, and accelerate the development of new
technologies and products and the formation of new industries, so
as to meet the demand of technical upgrading in enterprises,
readjustment of the industrial structure, and social development.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that China would propagate the use of advanced
and applicable technology in all aspects of agricultural
production, develop high and new technologies and related
industries, and speed up the research and development of
electronic information, biology, new materials, new sources of
energy, the sea, the environment, astronautics, aeronautics and
other fields.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government would also work for promoting the
commercialization and application in production of scientific and
technological achievements, and for upgrading the country's
traditional industries with high and new technologies, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We would strengthen basic research, particularly in fields on
the cutting edge of science and technology, and strive to make
breakthroughs in fields where we have been doing well," he said,
adding that continuous efforts should be made to deepen the reform
of management systems in science and technology, optimize the
structure, and encourage the flow of talented people, so as to
give full play to the role of China's existing scientific and
technological contingents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
