<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Keen on Re-employment of Displaced Workers (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- China will make keen efforts to
resolve the re-employment of displaced workers and to promote
reforms in the social security system, Premier Li Peng said today.
</P>
<P>
"Actively solving the re-employment problem is an important
channel to improving people's living standard and safeguarding
social stability," Li told the Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress, which opened today in the Great Hall
of the People.
</P>
<P>
As China'a restructure of its state-owned enterprises,
enterprise mergers and bankruptcies have displaced some workers,
prompting the government to take earnest measures for
re-employment of reduced workers.
</P>
<P>
"For some enterprises operating at a loss, provided they employ
workers in accordance with production needs and provided they can
increase efficiency while reducing their staff, we shall reduce or
exempt them from interest on government loans as appropriate,
assist the redundant workers in finding placement in other trades
and assist those who are laid off in finding new jobs," Li said.
</P>
<P>
In light of specific conditions, all localities should
establish re-employment funds out of contributions from local
finance, enterprises and social security funds, the premier urged.
</P>
<P>
"We should create more job opportunities, provide better
vocational training for employment, assist the laid off employees
in revising their job-seeking ideas and encourage them to find new
jobs on their own," he said.
</P>
<P>
And we should continue to encourage and help private and other
sectors of the economy to grow soundly and ensure that they play a
positive role in the modernization drive."
</P>
<P>
He noted that China shall introduce a unified system for basic
old-age insurance for employees and expand coverage.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time, we shall study ways to establish
supplementary old-age insurance for employees in enterprises and
trades where conditions permit," Li told the session. "In the
reform of the medical security system, we should focus on the
experiment in over 50 cities and continue to improve unemployment
insurance and work injury insurance."
</P>
<P>
Effort should be made to properly manage all types of social
security funds and improve services, the premier said.
</P>
<P>
At present, a system for ensuring a minimum standard of living
has been instituted in over 1200 cities, according to Li.
</P>
<P>
"This is a major step taken to guarantee the basic needs of the
people, a form of social security that conforms to China's
conditions. We should improve the system step by step," He said.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
