<HEADLINE> Chile to Spend More on Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean government will
allot 18.9 percent more money this year to promote the improvement
of water resources and irrigation.
</P>
<P>
The allocation will amount to 48 billion pesos (115 million
dollars). The Ministry of Agriculture will contribute 101.7
million dollars through the National Irrigation Commission and the
rest will come from another irrigation body.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Furche, Agrarian Studies and Policies Bureau director,
said public and private efforts must create inducements to make
more efficient the use of the resources. 
</P>
