<HEADLINE> Excerpts of Li Peng's Government Report (34) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua)-- China will expedite the shift of
the economic structure and the mode of economic growth
conscientiously to ensure stability and maintain a sustained,
rapid and sound development of the national economy and promote
social development in an all-round way.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng made this remark at the Fifth Session of the
Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The report, which falls in 36 pages and 17,000 Chinese
characters, is divided into seven parts. Based on reviewing the
government work last year, Li Peng concentrated on such topics as
economic development, reform of the state-owned enterprises and
social development.
</P>
<P>
The report also elaborated such issues as to ensure smooth
transfer of political power and a smooth transition in Hong Kong,
to promote the reunification of the motherland and the foreign
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li said the year 1996 was the first year in implementation of
the Outlined Ninth Five-Year Plan and Long-Range Objectives
through the Year 2010. Under the leadership of the Communist Party
of China, he said, the people of all nationalities in China
united, worked hard and achieved fresh success in the reform,
opening up and the modernization drive, making a good start for
the accomplishment of the magnificent cross-century program.
</P>
<P>
A salient feature of China's economic development in 1996 was
the continued growth in national economy and inflation under
control. The gross domestic product (GDP) increased by 9.7 percent
over the previous year and price rises dropped from 14.8 percent
to 6.1 percent, much lower than the planned target for
macro-control.
</P>
<P>
Besides, China's economic restructuring progressed steadily and
the country continued to open wider to the outside world. New
achievements were recorded in science, technology, education and
in all other social undertakings. The standard of living of urban
and rural people continued to improve.
</P>
<P>
However, the Chinese premier also pointed out there still exist
quite a few conflicts and problems in the midst of economic
development and public activities, and there are also shortcomings
and deficiencies in the work of the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
