<HEADLINE> Albania's Economic Situation Serious, Says PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister
Aleksander Meksi on Thursday described the country's economic
situation as serious.
</P>
<P>
Meksi made the remark at a special meeting of the People's
Assembly (parliament) which was discussing the bad social and
economic situation which had arisen from fake fund raisings
beginning in 1992 when the Democratic Party came into power.
</P>
<P>
Albania's situation was deteriorating because of the fake fund
raising. It had led to increases in budget deficits and the
inflation rate, and the fast devaluation of the country's
currency, said Meksi.
</P>
<P>
Albania hoped to get financial aid from the European Union
(EU), and was eager to sign three year loan agreements with the
International Monetary Fund, which should have been signed last
November.
</P>
<P>
But visiting EU officials said that aid to Albania would depend
on the development of the country's political and economic
situation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
