<HEADLINE> Li Peng on 1997 Economic Growth Rate (40) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Maintain a reasonable scale of investment and intensify
structural readjustment.
</P>
<P>
Giving a comprehensive consideration to the need to
accelerate economic growth and to the feasibility in terms of
financial and material resources, Li noted, the central
government has set the following objectives for macroeconomic
control this year: a total investment of 2,530 billion yuan in
fixed assets at an investment rate of 32 percent.
</P>
<P>
He said that the investment should continue to favor
agriculture and water conservancy projects, to favor
infrastructural facilities, basic industries and pillar
industries which receive major support from the state, to favor
the central and western parts of the country, to favor
technological upgrading, and to favor the fields of science,
technology and education.
</P>
<P>
"We should pool our funds to complete a number of key
projects of the state essential to the restructuring of the
economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the central government will strictly control the
launching of ordinary projects in the processing industry, and
avoid "large and all-inclusive" or "small and all-inclusive"
projects as well as duplicated construction.
</P>
<P>
"No project should be approved if production capacity in that
field is already excessive, and those already under construction
shall be carefully checked," he said, adding that reform of the
investment system should be accelerated and more effective
measures be taken to minimize investment risks.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government would work out plans for
structural readjustment and technological upgrading, and provide
guidance for enterprises so that they may adapt their production
to market needs and enhance their market competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
"Emphasis should be placed on expansion of the service
industry, and on tourism and the information industry, while
sound guidance should be provided for consumers so that
production and consumption may develop in a coordinated manner
and promote each other," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
