<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on 1997 Economic Growth Rate (39) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng said today in
Beijing that China in 1997 will continue to maintain a sustained,
rapid, and sound development of the national economy, fix the
economic growth rate at 8 percent as the target for macroeconomic
control, and make sure that price rises are a little lower than
they actually were last year.
</P>
<P>
In his government work report to the Fifth Session of the
Eighth National People's Congress, which started here today, Li
told the legislators that in order to maintain a good momentum of
growth in the national economy, the Chinese government will focus
on scoring success in the following five aspects of work:
</P>
<P>
-- Continue to give priority to strengthening agriculture in
the economic work.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the government would try to stabilize the area of
land sown to grain and cotton, take precautions against droughts
and floods, prevent grain production from decreasing, and promote
the all-round development of farming, forestry, animal husbandry,
sideline production, and fishery to increase farmers' incomes.
</P>
<P>
"We should maintain and improve the household responsibility
contract system with remuneration linked to outputs as well as the
two-tier operation system that combines unified management with
independent management," he said, adding that the grain
circulation system should be further reformed and the protective
pricing system further improved with a view to encouraging farmers
to produce.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government will make every effort to
facilitate a system of grain circulation, try by every means to
use as little land as possible in urban and rural construction,
and strictly control non-agricultural use of farmland.
</P>
<P>
He also said that it is an urgent task to strengthen the
construction of water conservancy facilities, establish central
and local water conservancy construction funding to increase input
in this field.
</P>
<P>
"We should also strengthen the development, comprehensive use
and management of water resources, vigorously develop water-saving
irrigation and dry-land farming, and combine flood control with
drought-relief," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0216 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on 1997 Economic Growth Rate (41) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Continue to carry out appropriately tight financial and
monetary policies.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the central government will maintain a measured
increase in the money supply, and restructure loans to improve
benefits from loans and to support production and construction.
</P>
<P>
"We should by no means relax control over price rises, as
pressure from inflation still exists," he said, adding that the
government will continue to implement the responsibility system to
attain objectives in price readjustment and control, and further
tighten supervision over and control of market prices.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government must try every means to increase
revenue and cut spending, gradually reduce deficits and control
the scale of debts.
</P>
<P>
"We must improve our taxation system and collect taxes in
strict accordance with the law, while strictly controlling
expenditures to ensure that expenditure increases do not exceed
revenues," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government will rectify the financial order,
investigate and severely punish illegal financial institutions and
any business activities in violation of the law or of regulations
so as to guarantee the safety of financial assets.
</P>
<P>
"We must enforce rigorous discipline in settling accounts,
safeguard the credit system, strengthen financial management of
enterprises and gradually usher in professional auditing
services," he said, adding that supervision over auditing should
also be strengthened.
</P>
</TEXT>
