<HEADLINE> Li Peng on 1997 Economic Growth Rate (43) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Continue to improve the standard of living of the people in
urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
Li said that on the basis of economic development, the
government will ensure a steady growth of income for people in
urban and rural areas, actively commercialize housing in cities
and towns, and improve the housing conditions for the people.
</P>
<P>
"We should increase the construction of infrastructural
facilities for public health in rural areas to prevent and cure
endemic diseases, extend the coverage of radio and television, and
improve transportation, communication and other public facilities
in urban and rural areas," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government will assist poverty-stricken people
in the countryside, and in 1997, the state will increase, by a
fairly large margin, funding in the form of "relief through work",
special loans to assist poor people, and development funds to
support underdeveloped areas.
</P>
