people in disaster areas, and take care of employees, including
retired ones, of enterprises which have totally or partially
suspended production, helping them to solve the problems vital to
their daily life.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the government will make every effort to
solve the problem of unemployment, and encourage those farmers who
have become skillful in various technologies and who have gained
managerial experience to return to their hometowns to start new
businesses there and to assist in the endeavor to shake
off poverty and become prosperous.
</P>
<P>
"We should also gradually straighten out the distribution
pattern, improve the taxation system, strengthen and improve the
collection and management of individual income tax, protect
lawfully earned incomes, outlaw extralegal earnings, and regulate
excessively high incomes," he noted.  
