<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Enterprise Reform a Focus of Economic Restructuring: Li Peng (44) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- State-owned enterprise reform is a
focal point of China's economic restructuring this year and a
pressing task for the government, Premier Li Peng said today.
</P>
<P>
China will make greater strides to reform state-owned
enterprises this year, Li told the Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress, the country's top legislature which
opened its annual meeting in the Great Hall of the People this
morning.
</P>
<P>
Over 60 percent of the state revenue comes from state-owned
enterprises and two-thirds of the employees in cities and towns
work in state-owned enterprises, according to Li, who said that
state-owned enterprises dominate the fields of infrastructure,
basic industry and high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
"The state sector of the economy has made a tremendous
contribution to the reform, development and stability of the
country," the premier said.
</P>
<P>
However, a number of state-owned enterprises are confronted
with difficulties and problems to varying degrees, he told the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
He added that one major cause is the management system, the way
the state firms operate and the concepts held by the managerial
staff are not compatible with a market economy.
</P>
<P>
Other major reasons for the difficulties and problems of the
state-owned enterprises include: structural readjustment does not
conform to changes in market demand and state-owned enterprises,
especially old enterprises and old industrial bases, have become
less potent in the market competition owing to heavy liabilities,
social burdens and over-staffing.
</P>
<P>
Li cited President Jiang Zemin as pointing out that the reform
and development of state-owned enterprises is not only a major
economic issue having a bearing on the overall development of the
national economy, but also a major political issue which is of
vital importance for the destiny of the socialist system.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China has stepped its effort aimed at
reforming state-owned enterprises and some measures have begun to
produce good results, the premier said.
</P>
<P>
"Our economic development is gaining momentum, economic reform
is deepening, and all sectors of society have recognized the
urgency and difficulty of the task of reforming enterprises," he
said.
</P>
<P>
We are convinced that we will be able to do a good job in the
reform and development of state-owned enterprises."
</P>
<P>
Li revealed that one major step China will take this year to
reform the state-owned enterprises is concentrating first on
rejuvenating 1,000 large state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 300 of the enterprises were given special financial
support by banks last year. This year the number of such
enterprises will reach 511.
</P>
<P>
The government has been experimenting with 57 enterprise groups
and will expand the experiment to 120 groups this year in order to
develop trans-regional and inter-trade enterprise groups which
combine industrial production, technological development and
trade, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Other substantial measures for state-owned enterprises include
giving small state-owned enterprises greater freedom,
standardizing bankruptcy procedures, encouraging merging of
enterprises and promoting re-employment, raising the number of
cities to experiment with capital structure optimization from 58
to 110, increase enterprises' capital and reduce their debts
through various channels, and strengthening the operation and
management of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"It should be our long-term basic policy to retain a dominant
position for public ownership and to develop diversified economic
sectors simultaneously," Li said, adding that the public sector of
the economy is comprised of state and collective enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"While reforming and developing state enterprises, we should
actively develop different forms of collective enterprises in
urban and rural areas. We should continue to encourage and help
private and other sectors of the economy to grow soundly and
ensure that they play a positive role in the modernization drive,"
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
