<HEADLINE> China Constitutes No Threat to Other Country (24) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- China will not join in the arms
race and a developed China will not constitute a threat to any
other country, said Li Peng, premier of the State Council today.
</P>
<P>
In the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's Congress
(NPC), which opened here this morning, Li Peng said China will not
engage in military expansion, and it will never seek hegemony, but
rather, it will remain a staunch force for safeguarding world
peace
</P>
<P>
On national defence, Li said, China will accelerate the
modernization of national defence, which is an important guarantee
for the economic development and long-term stability.
</P>
<P>
He urged governments at all levels to support the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA) in its efforts to carry out a
strategy of active defence and to take the road of "few but better
troops" with Chinese characteristics and to further increase
China's capacities in national defence.
</P>
<P>
China will conduct education among the people on the importance
of national defence and make a success of defence work with regard
to the militia and the reserves, he said, while emphasizing the
importance of consolidating unity between the army and the
government and between the army and the people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
