<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Emphasizes Socialist Democracy (25) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to develop
socialist democracy and improve the socialist legal system in
order to run state affairs according to law, Chinese Premier Li
Peng said today.
</P>
<P>
"Developing socialist democracy and improving the socialist
legal system are important aspects of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics and important guarantees for consolidating
and developing social and political unity and stability," Li said
at the opening of the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
China should continue to improve and develop democracy at the
grass-roots level, ensure the democratic rights of self-government
of both urban and rural people and fully arouse the people's
motivation to deal with their own affairs as masters of the
country, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that government employees should keep themselves
informed of conditions among the people, try hard to solve social
and economic problems which immediately affect the people's
interests, and do their best to help relieve the people's worries
and tide them over.
</P>
<P>
"Governments at all levels must conscientiously accept
supervision by the people's congresses and their standing
committees, actively support the work of the people's political
consultative conferences, take the initiative to strengthen
contact with all democratic parties and listen to the opinions of
people from all sectors of society," he urged.
</P>
<P>
He said that this year the State Council will consider and work
out plans for further streamlining its organizations and lose no
time in drawing up a number of laws and formulating a number of
administrative statutes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
