<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Hong Kong Issue (26) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The policy of "one country, two
systems" will be crowned with success, Hong Kong will maintain
long-term prosperity and stability, and the future of Hong Kong
will be even brighter with the support of all the Chinese people
and through the joint efforts of the more than six million people
of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
This remark was made by Premier Li Peng at the Fifth Session of
the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), which opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government will resume the exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong and establish the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
"This will mark the beginning of a new era in the history of
Hong Kong, which is a great joy for our compatriots both at home
and abroad," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the early 1980's, Deng Xiaoping proposed the concept of "one
country, two systems", pointing out clearly the direction for the
settlement of the Hong Kong issue. For over ten years, the Chinese
Government has done a great deal of work on the return of Hong
Kong to the motherland, he recalled.
</P>
<P>
In 1984, he said, the Chinese and British governments
officially signed the Sino-British Joint Declaration. In 1990, the
Third Session of the Seventh National People's Congress adopted
the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region of
the People's Republic of China. The Preliminary Working Committee
of the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region was established in July 1993. The
Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region was established in January 1996 to take charge of affairs
regarding the establishment of the HKSAR.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Hong Kong Issue (27) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the end of last year, he said, for the first time in the
history of Hong Kong, Hong Kong people elected the Chief
Executive-designate, Mr. Tung Chee Hwa, who was then commissioned
by the State Council in accordance with law as the Chief Executive
of the HKSAR. The Provisional Legislative of the HKSAR was also
elected and established.
</P>
<P>
There are only 122 days left until Hong Kong is returned to the
motherland, and all preparations are being made in an orderly
fashion. After China resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong, he said the Chinese government will adhere to the policy of
"one country, two systems" and implement the Basic Law
conscientiously, so as to ensure that the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region will enjoy a high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong people will govern Hong Kong, and the current social
and economic systems and way of life in Hong Kong will remain
unchanged. Hong Kong will retain its status as a free port and as
an international financial, trade and shipping center," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng pointed out in a little over two years, on December 20,
1999, the Chinese Government will resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Macao. Preparations for the transfer of
government in Macao are progressing smoothly. He expressed his
belief that on the basis of friendly cooperation between China and
Portugal, a smooth transfer of government in Macao will surely be
realized.  
</P>
</TEXT>
