<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Taiwan Issue (28) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng called on the
Taiwan authorities to return to the principled position of one
China, stop all activities in the international arena aimed at
creating "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan" and refrain from
creating any new obstacles to relations across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Fifth Session of the Eighth National People's
Congress (NPC), which opened this morning, Li said over the past
year, personal contacts have increased and economic and cultural
exchanges have continued to develop between the two sides of the
Taiwan Straits, with significant results achieved in the struggle
against the splitting of China and the "independence of Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
However, he said, due to obstruction and sabotage by forces
trying to split China, there have been some twists and turns in
contacts across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government will adhere to the basic policy
of "peaceful reunification" and "one country, two systems" and
carry out in an all-round way the eight-point proposal on
developing relations across the Taiwan Straits and promoting the
peaceful reunification of the motherland put forward by President
Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the one-China principle, the Chinese government
will settle disputes between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits
through political negotiations between the two sides and gradually
achieve the peaceful reunification of the motherland. It will
continue to promote personal contacts and all kinds of exchanges
and cooperation between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits and
try to realize direct links for postal, flight and shipping
services and trade at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out regardless of how they change the political
system of Taiwan, the Taiwan authorities should be aware that they
cannot change such a fact generally recognized by the
international community that Taiwan is a part of China.
</P>
<P>
He said the reunification of the motherland is an irreversible
historical trend, and any attempt at splitting China or at the
secession of Taiwan from China will meet with the firm opposition
of the entire Chinese people, including the compatriots in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that so long as we persist in reunification, oppose
splitting, increase understanding and iron out differences in
compliance with the fundamental interest of the Chinese nation,
the relations across the Taiwan Straits will develop continuously
and the great cause of reunification of the motherland will
definitely be achieved," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
