<HEADLINE> Mongolia Sets Presidential Election Date </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, February 28 (Xinhua) -- The Great Hural of Mongolia
(parliament) opened a special meeting on Friday and decided to
hold the presidential election on May 18.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also set the funds for the election at 150 million
togrog (about 202.6 thousand U.S. dollars), said the local report.
</P>
<P>
The election campaign will begin on March 5, and the
presidential nomination of suitable parties will be carried out
between March 12-26, said the report.
</P>
<P>
According to Mongolia's constitution, only parties which have
seats in parliament have the right to nominate candidates. They
are currently the Mongolian National Democratic Party, the
Mongolian Social-Democratic Party, the Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party and the Mongolian Traditional Union Party.
</P>
<P>
Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat, the country's incumbent president, will
end his term on June 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
