<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Made Quicker Steps in Application of Scientific Results(30) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- China has quickens its steps in
applying scientific and technological results into industrial
production, and the development of the high and new technology
sector.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists produced more than 2000 scientific and
technological results recognized as key national ones in 1996,
said Premier Li Peng when delivering the government report to
the opening meeting of the ongoing Fifth Session of the Eighth
National People's Congress today.
</P>
<P>
The results focused on agriculture, natural resources
prospecting, chief raw materials, major equipment, energy,
transportation, new technologies, the light and textile
industries, and social development.
</P>
<P>
Eighty out of ten new seed varieties in use are the results of
scientific and technological projects, which add more than 30
billion kg of rice, wheat, and corn. And the productivity medium-
and low-yield fields in the dry land in north China, the Loess
Plateau, areas troubled with soil erosion, and hilly land in south
China were improved.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological development created the condition
for China to have an autarkic grain supply.
</P>
<P>
Energy shortage is a major problem long troubling the Chinese
economy. Advanced technologies were applied in coal mining, oil
exploitation and power generation with nuclear energy, which
remarkably improved the general standards of energy utilization.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to scientific and technological progress, China has made
new breakthroughs in oil and gas exploration and comprehensive use
of non-ferrous metals. Nine large and medium oil and gas fields,
with reserves amounting to 500 million tons and 600 billion cu m
respectively, have been discovered in the Tarim Basin in northwest
China.
</P>
<P>
New technologies are being used on some railways, and the speed
of passenger trains has been elevated to 140 km per hour; while
tremendous economic efficiency have also been achieved in light
industry, with new techniques applied in production of integrated
circuits, computer systems and softwares, telecommunications
equipment and program controlled systems.
</P>
<P>
Adoption of new technologies has doubled the sewage disposal
capacity of Chinese cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
