<DOCNO> XIE19970301.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Follow Environment, Family Planning Policies (19) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said today
that China will conscientiously carry out the basic state policies
of environmental protection and family planning.
</P>
<P>
"The relationship between economic development and the
environment, population and resources must be correctly handled,"
Li said at the opening of the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
China should tighten environmental supervision and management
according to law, cope with serious pollution in major valleys,
regions and industries and improve the quality of drinking water
for people and livestock, he said.
</P>
<P>
" We should pay great attention to building urban pollution
control facilities to reduce pollution caused by waste water,
waste gases, other wastes and noise. We should protect and
appropriately develop sea, forest, grassland, mineral, biological
and other natural resources in accordance with the law," he said.
</P>
<P>
He called for efforts to actively expand afforestation, speed
up the plantation of shelter forests by the Yellow River, Liaohe
River, Pearl River, Haihe River and Taihu Lake valleys, and carry
on with the Northeast, North and Northwest China Shelter Forest
Project and the similar project in the upper and middle reaches of
the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
"We should not slacken our efforts in family planning as the
years go by," Li said, adding that China's goal in birth control
is to keep the total population under 1.3 billion by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, China will adhere to and improve the system under
which governments at all levels are responsible for attaining
given objectives in birth control, give priority to family
planning in rural areas and among the floating population and
combine family planning with efforts to assist farmers to shake
off poverty, the premier said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
