<HEADLINE> Indonesia Criticizes Israeli New Housing Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia has strongly criticized
Israel's decision to build houses for Jewish settlers in East
Jerusalem and called on the U.N. Security Council to take steps to
cancel Israel's decision.
</P>
<P>
"The Israeli government's decision violates and is opposed to
the peace agreement which has reached by the PLO (Palestine
Liberation Organization) and Israel," the Indonesian Foreign
Ministry said in a statement issued last night.
</P>
<P>
