year, said the Mexican Franchise Association.
</P>
<P>
The 400 firms that operate in Mexico under the franchise system
generate more than 150,000 jobs, and sell products under more than
400 trademarks.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Uruguay registered a 361 million dollar deficit
in 1996, accounting for 1.95 percent of its gross domestic product
(GNP).
</P>
<P>
The deficit reduction was less than estimated initially by the
government, which had estimated an inbalance close to 1.25 percent
for 1996.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Fiat, the Italian vehicle manufacturing firm,
confirmed plans to invest 200 million dollars in the Minas Gerais
Brazilian state to build a new plant to produce pickup trucks and
wagon vans.
</P>
<P>
