<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng calls for
consolidating and developing ethnic unity when he delivered the
government work report on the Fifth Session of the Eighth National
People's Congress here today.
</P>
<P>
The premier said economic and social development in areas
inhabited by the ethnic minorities has accelerated, the people's
standard of living has improved noticeably, and relations between
various ethnic groups are good. And "we should value and further
develop this good situation."
</P>
<P>
He noted it is essential to uphold and further improve regional
autonomy for ethnic minorities and guarantee autonomy for ethnic
minority areas and equal rights for all ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
"We should actively train cadres and all types of talented
ethnic minority people with a view to accelerating the development
of their economy and culture," Li Peng added.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that his government will unswervingly safeguard the
unity of the motherland and ethnic unity, and resolutely oppose
any words or activities designed to split the country or damage
ethnic unity.
</P>
<P>
Li added that the government will respect citizens' freedom of
religious belief, and will not discriminate against those with or
without religious belief.
</P>
<P>
