<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Investment Scale, Structural Readjustment (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Feasibility studies will be conducted carefully before
launching any new construction projects to ascertain whether or
not they are in line with the state industrial policies and plans
for the development of specific trades, whether their products
will be marketable, and whether there will be reasonable returns
from the investment, he said.
</P>
<P>
China will accelerate the reform of the investment system and
take more effective measures to minimize investment risks, he
said. A certain proportion of funds will go to profit-making
construction projects, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged to remove barriers between regions and
departments, vigorously developing diversified joint investment
and cooperative operation in order to avoid redundant
construction.
</P>
<P>
Li noted China will work out plans for structural readjustment
and technological upgrading and provide guidance for enterprises
so that they may adapt their production to market needs, actively
restructure their product mix, improve the quality of their
products, develop new products and new name brands and enhance
their market competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will also be made to vigorously develop markets,
especially rural markets, and offer more marketable products to
consumers in cities and the countryside.
</P>
<P>
He said China will also support the development of those
enterprises which produce marketable products and enjoy relatively
good economic returns, and cut down or adjust excessive production
capacity in some trades.
</P>
<P>
The central government will place emphasis on expansion of the
service industry, and on tourism and the information industry. It
will also provide sound guidance for consumers so that production
and consumption may develop in a coordinated manner and promote
each other, Li said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
