<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria, Macedonia Plan Trade Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria will further develop
economic ties with Macedonia, including the establishment of a
free trade zone, a corridor, cable and railway links.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Bulgarian caretaker government
Prime Minister Stefan Sofianski.
</P>
<P>
Sofianski said he and Macedonian Prime Minister Branko
Crvenkovski had agreed on these plans during an official visit he
made to Macedonia this week, the Bulgarian Telegraph Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to begin an expert-level discussion on
setting up the free trade zone and both would assign a bank for
trade clearances as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The cable between Sofia, capital of Bulgaria, and Skoplje,
capital of Macedonia, would be extended to their neighbors --
Albania and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The two countries would ask for support from international
financial institutions on the project of establishing the
corridor, and would try to get Albania, Italy and Turkey join the
project.
</P>
<P>
The trade value between Bulgaria and Macedonia during the first
three-quarters of 1996 reached 126 million U.S. dollars, 40
percent lower than the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
