<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Bankruptcy and Merging of Enterprises (13) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- China will standardize bankruptcy
procedures, encourage merging of enterprises and promote re-
employment while readjusting and reorganizing state-owned
enterprises to promote re-arrangement of assets and raise the
overall quality of the state sector of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in the government report delivered at the Fifth
Session of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC) today, Li
Peng, premier of the State Council said the Chinese government
conducted an experiment in 58 cities to optimize the capital
structure of enterprises, providing these enterprises with
preferential policies over the recent few years.
</P>
<P>
"This facilitated the re-organization and restructuring of
those enterprises," he said.
</P>
<P>
He told the deputies present this year that the experiment will
be expanded to 110 cities. Enterprise merger and the declaration
of bankruptcy are important ways of selecting the superior and
eliminating the interior, he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, China will increase capital reserves to be used in
selected cities to clear the bad debts of merged and bankrupt
enterprises. In declaring enterprises to be bankrupt, the Chinese
government will act strictly according to the law. The proceeds
from sell-off of the assets of bankrupt enterprises will be used
first to make arrangements for the employees and then to repay
debts.
</P>
<P>
"Bankrupt enterprises shall be closed and no enterprises shall
be allowed to evade payment of debts through declaring
bankruptcy," he said.
</P>
<P>
China will encourage the merger of enterprises. In selected
cities, merged enterprises will be allowed to repay the principal
on their bank debts within a fixed period of time and will be
exempt from paying the interest.
</P>
<P>
China will encourage the association of enterprises so that
they will be able to expand their scale of operation through
complementing one another with respect to their unique advantages.
The merger and association of enterprises should proceed on a
voluntary basis.
</P>
<P>
For some enterprises operating at a loss, provided they employ
workers in accordance with production needs and provided they can
increase efficiency while reducing their staff, China will reduce
or exempt them from interest on government loans as appropriate,
assist the redundant workers in finding placement in other trades
and assist those who are laid off in finding new jobs.
</P>
<P>
In light of specific conditions, he said, all localities should
establish re-employment funds out of contributions from local
finance, enterprises and social security funds.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese premier, China will create more job
opportunities, provide better vocational training for employment,
assist the laid off employees in revising their job-seeking ideas
and encourage them to find new jobs on their own.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
