<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Government to Promote Reform of Social Security System (16) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 1 (Xinhua) -- China will promote reform of its
social security system and circulation system to pave a way for
deepening enterprise reform, Li Peng, premier of the State
Council, said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening meeting of the Fifth Session of the
Eighth National People's Congress, Li said the Chinese government
will introduce a unified system for basic old-age insurance for
employees and expand coverage in the new year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he said, the government will study ways to
establish supplementary old-age insurance for employees in
enterprises and trades where conditions permit.
</P>
<P>
On reform of the medical insurance system, he said, the
government will focus on an experimental program being carried out
in over 50 cities. The government will continue to improve
unemployment insurance and work injury insurance, and efforts will
be made to properly manage all types of social security funds and
improve services, he said.
</P>
<P>
On reform of the circulation system, Li said the government
will develop and standardize chain stores, the proxy system for
foreign trade, goods distribution centers and other modern
marketing methods.
</P>
<P>
The premier called for strictly limiting the construction of
luxury emporiums, developing convenient shopping networks and
centers for urban and rural residents, rectifying market order,
opposing unfair competition, and improving and standardizing all
types of markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
