<HEADLINE> Women's World Cup Downhill Cancelled for Rain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 1 (Xinhua) -- The second race in the women's World
Cup downhill competition in Hakuba, Japan, was cancelled on
Saturday due to rain and rescheduled for Sunday, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasts Saturday morning predicted cloudy and windy
skies with intermittent rain or snow for the rest of the day but
clear skies for Sunday at Hakuba, in central Japan Alps.
</P>
<P>
The race Sunday will be the women's seventh and penultimate
downhill event this season. The eighth and last downhill will be
held in the World Cup season finale at Vail, Colorado in
mid-March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
