<HEADLINE> Joint Poland-Czech Army Planned </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Polish Defense Minister
Stanislaw Dobrzanski and his Czech counterpart, Miloslav Vyborny,
said Friday that the two countries would set up a joint army.
</P>
<P>
They told a news conference that the issues of the joint army
would be discussed during the coming joint meeting of foreign
ministers and defense ministers of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two defense ministers signed an accord on providing mutual
training for professional servicemen and non-military personnel.
</P>
<P>
Dobrzanski, who arrived here Thursday for a two-day visit to
the Czech Republic, has had talks with Chairman of the Czech
Chamber of Deputies Milos Zeman and Foreign Minister Josef
Zielenice.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that Poland and the Czech Republic, both
of which wanted to join NATO in the first batch, should further
their close cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
