<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Belorussia to Sign Border Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, February 28 (Xinhua)-- Belorussia plans to speed up
negotiations on the border division with Ukraine, the visiting
Belorussian Foreign Minister, Ivan Antonovich, said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two countries would sign the border agreement as soon as
possible, said Antonovich, who arrived here Thursday for a two-day
visit.
</P>
<P>
"Border division concerns not only our two countries, but also
the whole of Europe," Antonovich said during talks with his
Ukrainain counterpart, Gennady Udovenko. "The sooner the agreement
is signed, the safer Europe will be."
</P>
<P>
Udovenko said Ukraine and Belorussia had different attitudes
towards the eastwards expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO), but this would not affect bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Both ministers agreed that NATO's expansion should not create a
new Berlin Wall. "We have common interests over building the
European security system," Antonovich added.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also discussed regional cooperation between
Ukraine, Belorussia and Poland. They told a press conference
regional economic cooperation could be a successful model for
other European countries.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko said the Ukrainian Prime Minister would visit Poland from
March 17 to 18, aiming to broaden economic cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
