<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Bugno Wins 10th Stage in Tour de Langkawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Former world champion
Gianni Bugno scored his first victory by finishing first in the
10th stage of the Tour de Langkawi on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian led a pack of three to complete the 123.2-km stage
from Jeli to Gerik in 3 hours 1 minute and 26 seconds, edging out
John Tanner of Britain and Franz Hitz of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Bugno broke away from the main field in the last kilometer and
the leading trio crossed the line just 15 seconds ahead of the
pack, paced by American Frank McCormack.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, fellow Italian Luca Scinto of the MG Technogym team
retained his yellow jersey for a fifth consecutive day and kept
his 2-minute-and-24-second overall lead.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan Sergui Lavrenenko emerged as the top rider among
Asian participants and won the orange jersey for fifth time.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's 11th stage is a 189.4-kilometer ride from Kangar to
Penang state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
