<HEADLINE> Mexico Demands Cooperation in Anti-Drug Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, February 28 (Xinhua) -- Mexican Foreign Relations
Minister Jose Angel Gurria said today his country demands more
cooperation from the affected nations in Mexico's fight against
drugs.
</P>
<P>
He urged fuller recognition for Mexico's anti-drug efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican government made big efforts to eradicate drug
trafficking and money laundering, and it spent 1.5 billion U.S
dollars a year on this, Gurria said in a television statement.
</P>
<P>
Each year many men and women lost their lives in their fight
against drug trafficking .
</P>
<P>
For this reason, drug affected countries, especially United
States, should acknowledge Mexico's efforts.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the U.S. certification system, Gurria said that
what should be done was to cooperate, not certify, since drug
trafficking was a global phenomenon that needed international
cooperation. 
