<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Eliminates Cigarette Ads </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 1 (Xinhua) -- Anyone who has paid a recent
visit to this scenic city in east China might wonder where the
flashy cigarette advertisements which used to dot the city have
gone.
</P>
<P>
This month the capital city of Zhejiang Province was listed
among the country's first cigarette ad-free cities by the Ministry
of Public Health.
</P>
<P>
The city has experienced several debates in recent years as to
whether cigarette ads should be allowed in scenic areas of the
city. As a result, "Drive cigarette ads out of Hangzhou" became a
slogan jointly launched by government departments and citizens.
</P>
<P>
In the past year all the open-air cigarette ads in the city
have been eliminated. Many hoardings and bulletin boards which
used to carry cigarette commercials now carry anti-smoking
messages. 
</P>
