<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 1 (Xinhua) -- This major North China port city
is well prepared for the opening of the Eighth Tianjin Export
Commodities Fair scheduled for March 8.
</P>
<P>
About 550 exhibition stands and booths at the Tianjin Sports
Center have been ordered by Chinese enterprises, many of them from
central and western regions, which are eager for overseas
co-operation, according to officials of the fair's organizing
committee.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises which are authorized to do import and
export business, joint ventures and solely-overseas-funded
enterprises will also participate in the fair.
</P>
<P>
